title: quick skillet supper
directions: Cook ground beef in a large skillet until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain off pan drippings.
Stir in next 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Stir in sour cream and 1/2 can onion rings. Cook just until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with remaining onion rings.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine flour, corn meal, salt and pepper in pie plate; dip tomato slices, covering both sides.
Pour oil in 12-inch skillet; over medium heat, fry slices, a few at a time, until golden brown on both sides and heated through.
Drain on paper towels.
Add more oil to skillet if needed.

title: strawberry sauce for dessert
directions: Place strawberries in a bowl and add granulated sugar.
Mash slightly. Set the bowl in a moderately warm room.
Beat the butter to a cream. Add the powdered sugar gradually, working it in well. Add egg white, beaten stiff.
Just before serving, combine with the mashed strawberries.

title: chicken squares
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Add cream cheese, parsley flakes, onion and 1/2 of the butter.
Roll out crescent rolls and put filling on each one.
Fold and roll up over filling and secure with a toothpick.
Drizzle the rest of the butter over rolls.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: tomato salsa
directions: Drain tomatoes, combine with other ingredients.
The "heat" of the salsa depends on the type and amount of hot pepper you use. Great served with tortilla chips or thin slices of baguette.

title: mincemeat crips
directions: Combine mincemeat and apples in an 8-inch square pan.
Combine flour, rolled oats, brown sugar and butter; sprinkle over mincemeat mixture.
Press lightly.
Bake in preheated moderate oven about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together and let stand 1/2 hour at room temperature.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first ingredients together and pour into crust.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped peanuts.

title: pound cake(sour cream)
directions: Add rest of batter and sprinkle with rest of brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant and slice lengthwise into 1/2-inch thick pieces. Fry in oil until tender.
Drain on paper towels.
(Press with paper towels to get out as much grease as possible.)
Drain tomatoes and mushrooms; get as much juice out of the tomatoes as possible.
Mix with seasonings.
Layer eggplant, tomato mix, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Repeat and top with tomato sauce, Parmesan and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 60 minutes.
To make enough to fill a casserole dish (about 10 x 10-inch), you need to double.

title: mississippi pig loaf
directions: Beat eggs well.
In separate bowl, cream butter, add sugar, mix well.
Add flour in small amounts, gradually add vanilla.
Add whipping cream gradually to mixture.
Beat for 2 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and save grease.
Simmer onion (diced) and green pepper (diced) until onion is clear.
In large kettle combine beans, squeeze ketchup and mustard and handful of brown sugar.
Add onion, green pepper and crumbled bacon.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Wash spareribs and cut into 2 rib sections.
Arrange in baking pan with rack, sprinkle minced dried onions over ribs, then use garlic powder, oregano and pepper to your taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours, covered.
While baking, prepare barbecue sauce.

title: two layer coconut cake
directions: Bake Duncan Hines cake mix as directed.
Cool and split layers in half.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Combine everything except butter, milk and cornflakes.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix the butter and milk; pour over potato mixture.
Sprinkle with cornflakes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix and cool lemon jello, dash of salt and sugar in boiling water.
Add marshmallows (cut up), 1 cup milk and salad dressing; mix until jello is dissolved.
Let stand until begins to set.
Add 1 can fruit cocktail, drain, fold in whipped cream.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add first 4 ingredients and pulse 2 times or until blended.
Add margarine and lemon rind; process until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add lemon juice and egg; process until dough leaves sides of bowl and forms a ball.
Gently press mixture into a ball; wrap in heavy-duty plastic wrap and chill 1 hour.
Shape dough into 42 (1-inch) balls.; place 2 inches apart on baking sheets coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove cookies from pan and roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely on wire racks. Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.
Serving size:
1 cookie.

title: aunt eva's icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 5 to 6 minutes.
Beat until fluffy.
Frosts a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: scalloped tomatoes and artichoke hearts
directions: Grease shallow casserole.
Drain tomatoes and artichokes. Rinse artichokes and cut into quarters.
Saute onions and shallots in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, artichokes and basil.
Heat for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring gently.
Season with sugar, salt and pepper.
Turn into casserole and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are hot.

title: betsy's snap rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into buttered muffin pan.
Let set 15 minutes to rise. Bake in preheated 450° oven 15 minutes. Broil 1 to 2 additional minutes for a crisp brown top. Serves 6.

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar; beat until smooth.
Add anise extract and seed.
Add oil.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Batter will be sticky, but loose enough to be dropped by rounded teaspoonfuls.
(You can add more flour to reach consistency you want.)
Cook according to pizzelle maker instructions.
Makes about 36 to 40 pizzelles.

title: stuffed sandwiches
directions: Cook beef and onion; drain off grease.
Mix all ingredients including bread from hollowed out rolls.
Stuff this mixture evenly into rolls.
Brush top of rolls with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Freezes well, but thaw before baking or bread crust becomes too hard.
Great with French fries and a salad!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix with other ingredients. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees
Pour melted butter in a 13 x 9 pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly on top.
Sprinkle coconut, chocolate chips, peanut butter or butterscotch chips and top with sweetened condensed milk.
Sprinkle pecans on top and bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: "souper" chicken
directions: Cook and bone chicken, keeping them in as large a piece as possible.
Lay in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Combine broth and soups (do not dilute).
Pour this mixture over chicken. Prepare stuffing as directed on box and place with spoonfuls on top of soup and broth mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Wash jalapeno peppers and cut the ends off of the peppers. Take the seeds out of the peppers and stuff the cheese inside the peppers.
Take peppers and roll sausage around the peppers to make a small ball.
Roll the small ball in the Shake 'n Bake to cover. Bake at 375° until the sausage is done.
Make sure that you spray the cookie sheet with Pam before you place balls on it so you can cut down on the fat.

title: gooseberry pudding
directions: Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven 25
to
minutes.
When pudding comes out of the oven, put on topping.

title: gay hardy's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo, cream cheese and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Beat	until
well
mixed.
Start
in	cold oven. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: bette's macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 10 minutes, then drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine with rest of ingredients and put in baking dish.
Top with crushed cheese crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: marshmallow dessert
directions: Cream 1/4 cup of butter and add the cracker crumbs.
Spread in a pan, 8 x 10-inch.
Place in freezer.

title: sledge hammer
directions: In a gallon jug, mix ingredients. Let sit 30 minutes. Wrap a towel around the jug to keep cold.

title: bean dip
directions: Simmer beans in saucepan over medium heat.
When bubbling, turn down heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Take pan off stove and mash beans with potato masher.
Add sour cream and stir thoroughly.
Serve with chips.

title: cranberry pie with meringue top
directions: Boil sugar and water. Add cranberries and cook until they all pop. Add flour and butter. Cook 5 minutes. Add egg yolks and lemon juice.
Cook in double boiler until it thickens.
Cool.
Place in baked shell. Cover with meringue.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, unpeeled oranges and apples.
Dice celery. Add sugar; let set while mixing gelatin.
Combine when cool and add nut meats.
Let set overnight.

title: cheesy potato soup mix in a jar
directions: Layer the ingredients in the order given into a wide mouth 1 quart canning jar.
Pack each layer in place before adding the next ingredient.
Attach a gift tag with these cooking directions: Boil 8 cups water in a sauce pan over high heat.
Turn heat off. Slowly add soup mix, stirring constantly.
You may add 2 (5 ounce) cans heated ham, if desired.
Serve hot with your favorite bread or crackers.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash in small amount of boiling water until tender. Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients, except 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Stir gently.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: green and gold vegetables
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, in 1/2 inch boiling water heat onions, carrots, Brussels sprouts and 1 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Cover and cook for about 15 minutes or until fork tender. Drain; add 1 1/2 teaspoon salt and butter; toss gently.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa and soda together.
Mix water, salad dressing and vanilla. Add them to dry ingredients.
Beat by hand until well mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: amish cheese joes
directions: Fry together the hamburger, salt, pepper and onion.
Add water, catsup and oats.
Cook 1 minute.
Let set 5 minutes, then add soups.
Put on buns while hot with a slice of cheese.

title: apple relish
directions: Core apples and cut in pieces.
Cut orange in pieces and remove seeds if any.
Place apples and oranges in food processor and chop for about 1 minute.
Place in bowl.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Tastes like pumpkin.

title: fat free oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheets with cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients and raisins.
Add egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla.
Stir until well blended (dough will be stiff).
Drop by spoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes or just until firm.
Do not overbake.
Remove.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.
Each cookie provides 0 grams fat, 0 milligrams cholesterol, 60 calories, 1 gram protein, 13 grams carbohydrates, 65 milligrams sodium.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients together in large boiler.
Cook until done.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
When done, add tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes.

title: tea time cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix in all ingredients except pecans.
Chill, then form into ball.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: First make brownies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle with chocolate
syrup, then top with crushed Heath bars.
Cool.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Combine rice, half of the cheese, 1 egg and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Press firmly into bottom of a 9-inch pie pan or an 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Grate cabbage
and 2 carrots. Dice celery, pepper and onion. Mix all together.

title: beef stew(crock-pot)
directions: Cook in crock-pot about 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot-apple crumb pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line a 9-inch deep-dish pie plate with one crust (save the other one in the freezer or refrigerator); trim and flute edges.
Combine apples, 1/4 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup apricots and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Transfer to pie crust.
Combine remaining ingredients, sugar and apricots with fingers until it resembles coarse bread crumbs; sprinkle over apples.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 30 minutes; cool.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Slightly brown the ground beef with the onion.

Add celery which has been partially cooked in very little water and drained. (May want to save some celery water if mixture looks too dry.) Add cooked rice, soy sauce, soups, salt and almonds (optional). Mix well.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven in slightly greased baking dish.
The last 15 minutes, sprinkle with chow mein noodles.
Brown as desired.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package, omitting butter. Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in skillet.
Add mushroom caps; cook and stir until lightly browned. Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Cook and stir chopped mushroom stems and the peppers in the skillet until tender; stir into prepared stuffing.
Spoon onto mushroom caps; drizzle with 3 tablespoons butter.
Place under preheated broiler for 5 minutes to heat through.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Heat sugar
and
syrup	in saucepan until sugar is dissolved. Add peanut butter; mix in Rice Krispies.
Pack in 9 x 13-inch greased
pan.
Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips. Spread over top.
Refrigerate.	Cut
when top is set.
Yields 20 bars.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together well the graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter, margarine and powdered sugar.
Press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips over hot water; spread over the mixture in pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
(These can also be frozen.)

title: meryl's chocolate pie
directions: In a pan mix everything together except the vanilla.
Cook and stir over a low flame until thick.
Add vanilla, mix.
Pour into 9 inch pie crust.

title: cherry tart
directions: Whip cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla all together.
Place Dream Whip on top of cream cheese.
Place pie filling on top.

title: my sister's nutmallow goodies
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips on low heat; add peanut butter and melt until smooth.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows and peanuts; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on foil and chill until firm.

title: noodle strudel
directions: Cook noodles in salted water (1 teaspoon).
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients.
Put into casserole and top with extra cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: colin's cherry soup
directions: In saucepan, place cherries, about 2 cups water and sugar to taste.
Bring to boil.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour half into shallow baking dish; add potatoes.
Top with remaining syrup.
Bake at 350°, basting often, for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: shrimp joanna
directions: Melt butter and saute garlic and onion.
Add raw shrimp, mushrooms, parsley, paprika, hot sauce, cayenne pepper and Natures Seasons.
Cook until the shrimp turn pink.
Do not overcook shrimp!

title: pink stuff
directions: Dissolve jello and pineapple (in juice) in pan over low heat. Remove from heat and add buttermilk.
Put in refrigerator until partially congealed, maybe 2 hours.
Fold in remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: May use additional strawberries and Cool Whip for decoration on top.

title: french pastry
directions: Spread 1 can of rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Stir cream cheese, sugar and egg yolk until well beaten. Spread mixture over crescent rolls. Spread second can of rolls on top. Beat egg white until frothy. Spread over top. Sprinkle chopped nuts over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and wine
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 package of onion soup mix in pan.
Arrange a cut up frying chicken on top.
Mix together the mushroom soup, wine and water.
Pour over chicken. Cover with heavy-duty Reynolds Wrap.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Uncover.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Mix the cream cheese and mayonnaise well. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into loaf pan or refrigerator pan. Freeze 3 to 4 hours or put in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: german nut cake
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add sugar and stir together.
Add flour, sifted with a pinch of salt, the baking powder and the spices. Dredge almonds in a little flour and fold in.
Add flavoring. Bake in a large, shallow pan in a 350° oven, raising heat gradually to 375°.
Bake from 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool cake in the pan.
Cut in squares.
Recipe makes 1 large cake.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Cut top off tomatoes; take out centers.
Beat cream cheese. Blend in other ingredients.
Use 1/2 teaspoon in each tomato, then chill.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans; spread into well-greased and floured 8 x 14-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Pour over pecan and coconut mixture at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and stick of margarine in blender.
Add powdered sugar and blend until smooth.
Drizzle over cake as a topping.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° to 330°.
Test with toothpick.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss diced red apples with lemon juice.
Add diced celery, walnut pieces and mayonnaise; mix well.
Serves 4.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Place giblets (except liver) in pan.
Cover with water.
Add salt, 2-3 celery leaves and an onion slice.
Cover with lid and cook for 2 hours.
Add liver and simmer additional 20-30 minutes. Let cool.
Remove giblets from water, drain, and chop.
Also chop egg.
Mix in saucepan milk, flour or cornstarch, broth, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir constantly.
Add giblets and chopped egg and cook till warm.

title: baked crab dip
directions: Combine
cream
cheese,
milk and Worcestershire sauce. Drain, pick
and flake crabmeat.
Add to cream cheese mixture along with
onion.
Turn
into small, greased, shallow baking dish
or an
8-inch
pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with crackers.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and peanut butter.
Add white sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Shape into balls; roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Place chocolate kiss on each; press firmly.
Return cookies to oven.
Bake 2 to 5 minutes until golden brown.
Makes around 3 dozen.

title: white sangria
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Combine wine, Triple Sec and sugar. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add soda.
Garnish with citrus slices for decoration.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Grease and flour 9X13 inch pan.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix oleo, flour and nuts; pat into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes in oven at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: kosher pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Place grape leaf, dill, garlic and pepper in bottom of jar.
Pack cucumbers in hot, clean jars.
Mix vinegar, water, salt and alum in large pan; bring to boil.
Pour over top of cucumbers.
Place grape leaf, dill, garlic and pepper on top of cucumbers.
Seal jars.
Place in hot water bath for about 20 minutes in boiling water to seal jars.
Makes 8 to 9 quarts.

title: puff pie
directions: Strip cream out of cookies.
Crush cookies to coarse crumbs and set aside.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin in the cold water. Let stand 10 minutes.
Add hot water.
Stir and let cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar; mix with electric mixer.
Fold in gelatin mixture.
Whip the whipping cream.
Fold it into egg whites and gelatin mixture.
Add vanilla to taste.
Layer half the crushed crumbs into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour mixture on top. Top with remaining half of crumbs.
Freeze overnight.
Serve frozen.

title: chili con queso
directions: Slice and saute onions; leave in large strings.
Put all ingredients into a crock-pot and heat until hot.
Eat with chips or crackers.

title: bean and vegetable tacos
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Wrap tortillas in foil; bake 8 to 10 minutes or until soft and heated through.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook chopped onion in bacon fat until it becomes transparent. Combine flour, vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper with bacon fat and onion.
Stir constantly, cooking until thick.
Add sliced potatoes and crumbled bacon to dressing.

title: easy lemon chess pie
directions: Cut lemon in cubes and remove seeds.
Cut margarine in small pieces.
Place all ingredients in blender and blend thoroughly (about two minutes).
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Delicious with or without whipped cream.

title: chicken fried steak with gravy
directions: Cut steak in pieces.
Salt and pepper each slice.
Dip in milk and egg.
Roll in flour.
Place in skillet with 1-inch deep cooking oil.
Brown and cook on one side about 15 minutes over medium heat. Turn meat and repeat process.
When steak is done, remove slices and drain on paper towels.
Pour off most of oil, reserving 4 tablespoons fat and any meat crunchies.
Return to heat.
Make gravy.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until just tender; drain well. Mix with soup.
Place in 3-quart casserole; arrange chicken on top of noodles.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake, covered, in preheated 350° oven for one hour or until chicken is tender.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients with mixer.
Add water.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes one shell.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Put in pan with enough cold water to cover and cook until tender, but not done.
Drain; transfer potatoes to a
casserole.
Combine sugar and flour; add 2 cups water.
Pour mixture over the potatoes.
Dot with butter. Cook in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until liquid is thick.

title: puppy chow for kids
directions: Melt butter, then blend in chocolate chips and peanut butter until melted.
Pour warm mixture over dry cereal.
Mix well, then pour the powdered sugar over all.
Mix well and shake in a large container.
Cool and enjoy.

title: beef stew and biscuits
directions: Cook on low 3 to 4 hours.
Add 6 medium potatoes (cut up) and 1 lb. carrots (cut small).
Add any other vegetables you would like. Cook for 30 minutes on medium heat. Top with drop biscuits.

title: pistachio meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Line 2 large baking sheets with aluminum foil; butter and flour foil.
Mix chopped pistachios and 1/2 cup powdered sugar in small bowl to blend.
Beat egg whites and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar in medium bowl until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 2/3 cup sugar, beating until whites are stiff but not dry.
Fold nut mixture into egg whites.
Drop meringue onto prepared sheets by rounded tablespoonfuls, spacing 1-inch apart and spreading to form 2 1/2-inch rounds.

title: green bean and onion salad
directions: Cook beans until done but still firm.
Drain, add onions, salt, pepper and other ingredients.
Toss and serve at room temperature.

title: barbecue(using corned beef)
directions: Mix thoroughly and simmer for best flavor.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Soften cream cheese and combine all ingredients.
Spread into round pie dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 370° for 15 minutes.
(Can use frozen crabmeat.)

title: dixie pecan pie
directions: Blend together shortening and sugar; stir in pecans.
Set aside.
Mix together corn syrup, eggs, salt, milk and vanilla. Pour over shortening and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange sugared nuts
directions: Boil until it forms a soft ball.
Remove from stove, add nuts. Stir until it begins to whiten.
Lift out nuts, put on waxed paper.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: easy dipped cookies
directions: Melt coating according to package.
Spread peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers.
Dip in melted coating.
Let cool on foil or waxed paper.
Delicious.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup (from can of chilled) V-8 juice. Heat rest of V-8 to boiling point.
Combine all V-8 and add rest of ingredients, except celery.
Wet mold(s) and fill.
Let set a little in refrigerator.
Stir in celery.
Set, unmold and serve with curried mayonnaise.

title: pink dip
directions: Beat all ingredients until creamy.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Beat the sugar, oil and eggs. Add the remaining ingredients. Blend all together and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in greased tube pan lined with waxed paper.

title: pineapple congealed salad
directions: Add 1/2 of the boiled water called for on the box.
Add both boxes of Jell-O and bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add the crushed pineapple and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Cool and sit in icebox until thickened.
Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese, celery, nuts and marshmallows and top jelled mixture.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: In large bowl of an electric mixer, beat butter and sugar until creamy, then beat in eggs and lemon juice.
In another bowl, stir together flour, salt and baking soda; gradually add to butter mixture, blending thoroughly.
Add oats, raisins and walnuts and stir until well combined.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix first five ingredients together well. Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt stick of margarine and drizzle over top.
Cover with crumbled corn flakes.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh fruit chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package, using 2 cups skim milk. Stir in vanilla.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter or margarine and confectioners sugar until fluffy in medium size bowl; stir in flour gradually, then pecans until well blended.
Chill several hours or until easy to handle.
Roll dough into marble size balls; place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes or until lightly golden.
Cool on cookie sheets 5 minutes; dip in confectioners sugar.

title: "rizogalo" rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and water and boil until water is almost absorbed.
Add milk; simmer until rice is tender, about 25 minutes.
Add sugar and simmer until thick; remove from heat.
Add salt and cook over low heat about 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add vanilla.
Pour into pudding dishes; sprinkle with cinnamon. Serves 6.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cut Jack cheese into strips; mix sour cream and chiles.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Season rice with salt and pepper. Layer rice, sour cream mixture and cheese strips (in that order). Finish with rice on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and allow to melt.

title: cabbage casserole(quick stuffed cabbage)
directions: Chop cabbage. Spread in bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Brown meat and onion. Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture over cabbage.
Heat tomato soup and water.
Pour over ingredients. Cover casserole with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: egg substitute baked custard
directions: Scald milk until crinkly film forms on top.
In a bowl, slightly beat together egg substitute, sugar and salt.
Pour scalded milk into egg mixture in bowl.
Next, add vanilla flavoring to this mixture.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle nutmeg on top of mixture.
Set baking dish in a pan of hot water. Bake at 350° in preheated oven 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Mix 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, soda and salt. Heat 2 cups milk and 1/2 cup water. Add to dry mixture and stir. Add 3 more cups flour. Grease 2 loaf pans and sprinkle with corn meal. Divide dough into the 2 loaf pans. Let dough rise approximately 45 minutes. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups all-purpose flour and yeast in large mixing bowl.
Heat milk, sugar, butter and salt in saucepan until warm; stir into yeast mixture.
Add eggs.
Beat at low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in whole wheat flour and as much remaining all-purpose flour as possible.
Knead on floured surface for 5 to 8 minutes or until smooth and elastic. Place in greased bowl, turning to grease surface.
Let rise, covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down.
Let rest, covered, for 10 minutes.
Shape into rolls on baking sheet.
Let rise, covered, for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen.

title: strawberry short cake
directions: Go by recipe on cake mix.
Mash strawberries up.
Cook cake in pound cake pan.
Cool cake.
Slice cake in thin slices.
Mix strawberries and Cool Whip together in large bowl.
Put layer of cake and layer of strawberries and Cool Whip until all is used up.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix cheese and 1/2 cup milk.
Add the rest of the milk and pudding.
Beat.
Put in graham crust.

title: pistachio bavarian
directions: Place 1/2 cup milk in small saucepan.
Sprinkle gelatin over milk.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Cook milk over low heat, stirring occasionally until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour into a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups milk and instant pudding.
Beat with a wire whisk or rotary beater for 2 minutes or until mixture begins to thicken.
Gently fold in thawed whipped topping until blended.
Pour into a 5 cup mold.
Chill for 3 hours or until firm.
At serving time, unmold pistachio mixture on serving plate. Spoon a small amount of strawberry mixture on top of mold. Garnish mold with chopped pistachios, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef hors d'oeuvres
directions: Note:
You can also use "Roses" marmalade with this; lime marmalade from "Roses" tastes very good.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan over low heat.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fried spinach
directions: Wash spinach thoroughly and drain off excess water. Heat oil in a large wok or skillet. Add spinach and fry over fierce heat for 1 minute, stirring all the time with a chop stick, until spinach softens. Add salt and soy sauce, mix well and cook gently for another minute until spinach is tender and very bright green. Remove from wok and serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare soup with milk; heat to boiling.
Fill empty can with rice; add to boiling soup.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 10 minutes, then stir.
Set aside.
Cook broccoli and corn; drain.
Add to rice mixture.
Add green pepper, salt and pepper.
Pour everything into a greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, until heated through.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: party casserole
directions: Salt and pepper beef to taste.
Add oregano to taste.
Mix all ingredients and bake in greased casserole for 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick of oleo and graham cracker crumbs with pastry blender.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: meatball appetizer
directions: Combine jelly and chili sauce in large saucepan or crock-pot. Stir until well mixed, then add meatballs.
Cook on low for several hours.
Serve with sauce.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Crumble several slices of leftover meat loaf in casserole. Mix in green beans and gravy.
Spread mashed potatoes over top, like a crust, to cover.
Place cheese slices on top.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 40 minutes or until warm and bubbly.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown meat, if using hamburger.
Add onions, celery and tomato juice.
Add hot catsup.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Keeps indefinitely.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with 1 1/2 to 2 cups mushrooms which have been sauteed in margarine.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: crazy coconut pie
directions: Blend in blender until mixed.
Bake in large glass pie plate at 350° for 55 or 60 minutes.

title: picante corn muffins
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add buttermilk, eggs or egg substitute, picante sauce and butter last.
Stir just until ingredients are blended. Fill 12 well-greased muffin cups almost full.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes. Use a tube pan for baking.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, and eggs.
Beat well.
Add soda.
Add mashed bananas last.
If desired, add nuts.
Bake in two loaf pans at 325° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: "pop's" pound cake
directions: Have the powdered sugar and butter at room temperature and cream with mixer.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat well after adding.
Add the rum flavoring.
Add the sifted flour, but use only 3 cups at this time, and the baking powder to the creamed mixture with a large spoon (no mixer).
The extra flour may be needed, subject to weather and humidity.

title: hot butter rum mix
directions: Soften butter; cream in brown sugar, then powdered sugar.
Add in cinnamon and nutmeg and beat well.
Fold in ice cream.
Store in tightly sealed container in freezer.
Mix to taste with hot water; add rum, if desired.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; set aside.
Beat eggs slightly in large bowl.
Add sugar and oil; beat until creamy. Add vanilla.
Add zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring until mixed.
Batter will be thin.
Spoon into 2 or 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together biscuit mix, cheese and pepper. Stir in beaten eggs, just until mixture is moistened. Fold in zucchini.
In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Using 2 tablespoons mixture for each round, cook for 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until brown.
Keep warm until served. Makes 12 rounds or 6 servings.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Make a well in the flour and add all ingredients, mixed together.
Work in flour with clean hands until dough is firm. Roll out thin and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 350° until light brown on cookie sheet.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll in a ball, then roll in chopped pecans.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add jello and vanilla.
Cool.
Pour the thickening over the strawberries, after you divide the strawberries between the two pie shells.
Refrigerate and top with Cool Whip.

title: hidden valley dip
directions: Add all the above ingredients together and mix well. Refrigerate.
Excellent with all kinds of cut up vegetables.

title: orange sponge cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Make a well and add oil, egg yolks, liquid and orange rind.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until whites are stiff.
Fold into preceding mixture.
Bake in a tube pan or Bundt pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Turn oven to 350° and bake 10 minutes more.
Cool before icing.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over bran flakes.
Add Crisco.
Stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir together.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 22 minutes.
(Better if batter is chilled.) Batter will keep in refrigerator for 6 to 7 weeks.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: freezer ice cream(5-quart)
directions: Mix all together and pour into freezer.
Finish filling with milk.
Freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.

title: jessica's cheese sticks
directions: Slice bread into thin sticks.
Roll in melted margarine, then in Parmesan and paprika.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Enjoy.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package. When cooled, cut into small cubes.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Crush Heath bars into very small pieces.
In a large bowl, place some cubes of cake.
On top of that, alternate 1 heaping tablespoon of chocolate pudding and Cool Whip.
Top with Heath bars, then layer of cake and repeat the steps.
Top with Cool Whip and Heath bars.
Keep cool.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 15 x 2-inch pan.
Blend all dry ingredients together with a whisk until thoroughly mixed. Slowly add the melted butter, milk and eggs.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until toothpick comes out dry.
Check after 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Then remove from the pan.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: pumpkin cookies and icing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter or shortening and sugar together.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients; blend well.
Add nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and frost.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Serve with a sprinkling of oil, fresh chopped basil, salt and pepper.
Serve with raw spinach, onions and anchovies.
Serve with cucumbers, dill, oil and vinegar.
Or serve with a sprinkling of oil, a dash of vinegar, chopped onions and oregano.
Serve with mayonnaise.
Serve in a sandwich with lettuce, bacon and cheese. Serve with sour cream and chives.

title: chocolate chip raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream white and brown sugars with shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix until moist.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add gelatin; cool.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill and put whipped cream or Cool Whip on top. Garnish with berries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: oven baked stew
directions: Mix and bake, covered with foil, at 325° for 4 hours.
Serve over rice, cooked potatoes, or noodles.

title: christmas coffee cookie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Can be put in refrigerator as icebox cookies by adding 1/2 c more flour.
Can add chocolate chips.
Can form logs and roll in colored sugar to slice and bake.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Place in bottom of casserole.
Place 4 thin slices of American cheese.
Steam vegetables until tender. Drain vegetables. Toss with salt.
Pour over cheese.
Combine the sour cream, soup and enough sweet milk to make these pourable and put over casserole.
Place 4 thin slices cheese on top. Cover all with crumbled potato chops. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's tea cakes(old family recipe)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a separate bowl.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Stir in almond extract, cover and chill one hour.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness on a floured surface.
Cut with 2 3/4-inch round cookie cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and cauliflower.
Put in a large casserole dish.
Take 1/2 stick margarine and cut in slices.
Put on broccoli mixture.
Cut Velveeta into small squares.
Lightly toss into broccoli mixture.
Crush the crackers; put over broccoli.
Melt other half of margarine; pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
This is something that is easy and even picky children will like.

title: crispy chicken sticks
directions: Rinse and pat dry chicken.
Combine cornflakes, cornmeal, cheese and red pepper.
Dip chicken in flour and sprinkle with water.
Roll in cornmeal mixture.
Place on nonstick cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Combine flour, butter or margarine and undrained pineapple. Cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add chicken stock, fresh green pepper and celery.
Season to taste.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: sky-high brownie pie
directions: Spray a 9-inch microwave-safe pie plate with nonstick spray coating.
In a medium mixing bowl prepare the brownie mix batter according to package directions.
Spread evenly in the prepared pie plate.
Micro-bake according to package directions.
Transfer to wire rack; cool completely.

title: garlic dill pickles
directions: Boil this mixture; pour over cucumbers in jars.
Add garlic cloves and dill to each jar and seal.
Set 14 to 21 days before serving.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt shortening in small pan; set aside.
Mix flour, buttermilk and melted shortening.
Mix, adding water slowly (the dough will be soft).
Place dough on floured wax paper and knead (just a few times).
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place a small amount of melted shortening in baking pan and place biscuits in pan.
Brush top of each biscuit with melted shortening.
Bake for about 15 minutes, or until bottoms are brown. Broil to brown tops.
Makes about 6 biscuits.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Dissolve poppy seed in warm water.
Set aside while mixing cake mix and pudding.
Add eggs, one at a time, oil and poppy seed with water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sesame broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of boiling water until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and keep warm.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small pan and bring to a boil over medium heat. Pour over broccoli, turning pieces to coat well.
Serve immediately.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice; let cool.
Add the rest of ingredients plus enough mayonnaise to mix.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil together first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Take the spices out then add Lipton tea, orange juice, pineapple juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Heat up to drink, do not boil.
This is good on a cold winter morning or if you're feeling a bit under the weather.

title: angel pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.
(Can also use self-rising flour but do not add baking powder.)

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Combine eggs, sugars, peanut butter, shortening and vanilla. Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until thoroughly mixed. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add flour mixture to peanut butter mixture. Mix until blended. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Cut in bars while still warm. If desired, frost.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas. Put in egg and beat. Add oil and beat.

title: wassail
directions: Combine tea and juices.
Stir the sugar, cinnamon sticks and cloves into the hot tea.
Heat and serve or good cold.

title: cheddar broccoli noodles
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, heat water to boiling.
Add noodles and broccoli.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until noodles and broccoli are tender, stirring occasionally to separate noodles.
Add 1 seasoning packet (reserve remaining seasoning packet for another use); drain off most of the liquid.
Stir in cheese soup, sour cream and pepper. Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Top with sweet red pepper if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Mix and add the rest of ingredients.
Drop on wax paper.

title: four layer chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix margarine, brown sugar, flour and pecans together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake approximately 20 to 25 minutes until light brown.
Cool.

title: nachos
directions: Place tortilla chips on cookie sheet.
Top with piece of cheese, then a piece of pepper.
Heat under broiler until cheese is melted.
(Must be served hot!)

title: mama's creamed spinach
directions: Heat slowly the white sauce.
Add spinach and onion.
Stir until spinach is defrosted and serve.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add onion.
Add beaten egg and milk, stirring lightly.
Drop a teaspoon of batter for each hush puppy into fat heated to 360°.
Fry only a few at a time until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve with fried fish.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix first five ingredients. Pour fruit on top. Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes or until done.

title: baska bread
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, eggs, salt, shortening, anise, saffron and half the flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add raisins and remaining flour.
Turn onto floured board; knead until smooth.
Let rise; shape into loaves or put in coffee or shortening cans.
Let rise again.
Heat oven to 425°. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans.
When cool, frost with a powdered sugar frosting.
Sprinkle with candy sprinkles.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: scallops o'malleynamed for an irish lass who liked this dish because it was green.
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients; knead together.
Add a dash of Anisette.
Rinse scallops in cold water; sprinkle with a few drops of lemon juice.
Poach scallops in dry vermouth, slightly.
(In small pan, bring the vermouth to a boil, reduce flame and add a layer of scallops.
Swirl around the remove.
Repeat until all scallops have been poached.)
Mix the drained scallops with the spinach mixture.
Place in a baking dish; bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4.

title: crispy cole slaw
directions: Heat sugar, mustard, corn oil, vinegar and celery seed.
Pour while hot over the cabbage.
Seal tightly and put in refrigerator immediately.
Keep refrigerated.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: fire cracker burgers
directions: In a medium bowl, combine beef, chili peppers and bouillon. Mix together well and shape into 4 burgers. Grill burgers for 3 to 8 minutes per side until desired doneness. Top each burger with cheese 2 minutes prior to removing from grill.

title: warm pineapple sundaes
directions: Combine juice, sugar, water and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir well.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in pineapple, raisins, margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook over low heat, stirring until heated.
Stir in vanilla.
Place 1/2 cup or so of ice cream in dessert dish.
Spoon 3 tablespoons warm pineapple sauce over ice cream.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon toasted coconut, if deserved. Serve immediately.

title: italian eggplant
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and garlic until onion is transparent. Add eggplant and green pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Chill overnight.
May be kept refrigerated for 2 weeks.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add onion, garlic and mushrooms, then 2 cans of soup; heat thoroughly.
Turn stove on low temperature
and add sour cream.
Serve over noodles with garlic bread.
Do not boil sour cream.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour.
Mix in baking powder and salt. Work in shortening.
Pour in milk.
May need a little more milk.
Flour board and knead dough a little.
Dough will be soft and sticky. Place small amount of flour in hands.
Roll lightly a small amount of dough into a ball.
Place on greased pan.
Cook at 400° until lightly brown.
Place butter on top of biscuit and return to oven until golden brown.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk; coat with cheese mixture.
Place in baking dish; pour margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: creamy frosting for sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar and margarine. Stir in vanilla and milk. Beat until smooth and of spreading consistency. Can be doubled. Divide and add food coloring as desired.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix together and cook for 20 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry the chicken breast.
Spray both sides with butter spray and sprinkle with dressing mix.
Spray glass baking dish and put in chicken.
Bake for one hour, uncovered, at 350°.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Blend shortening into flour and salt with pastry blender. Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Pour egg mixture into flour is moistened.
Easy to handle.
May be rerolled without becoming tough.
Keeps for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together; blend in shortening well. Sprinkle water over mixture.
Mix and shape into balls.
Roll out thin.
This makes 3 (9-inch) pie crusts.
May be wrapped in foil and stored in refrigerator for several days.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix lemonade and Eagle Brand milk together well.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Let chill in refrigerator overnight.
Enjoy.

title: stuff baked potatoes
directions: Cut baked potatoes in half and scoop out the pulp.
Place in mixing bowl.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Combine ingredients and stir.
Gradually increase speed of mixer.
Beat until potatoes are fluffy.
Spoon potato mixture into shells.
Place on baking sheet and sprinkle with paprika. Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Grated cheese may also be sprinkled on top, if desired.

title: french cream pie
directions: Scald sugar and 2 cups milk in top of double boiler; mix egg yolks, cornstarch and 2/3 cup milk until smooth.
Add to milk mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire. Add pinch of salt, vanilla and butter.
Stir until butter melts. Add grated coconut.
Pour into cooled, baked pie shell.
Top with meringue or use whipped cream.
Also makes a good banana cream pie.

title: four cheese pasta and beef
directions: Cook pasta as directed and drain.
In skillet brown meat with salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and cook uncovered until slightly thickened.
Stir in onions and cream cheese.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Cover 2 minutes to melt cheese. Yields 4 to 6 servings.
Preparation and cooking time is 30 minutes.

title: broccoli with ripe olive sauce
directions: Saute garlic in oil in small saucepan over medium-low heat until golden, about 3 minutes; do not let brown.
Discard garlic. Add olives, lemon juice, salt and pepper to oil; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Trim broccoli; divide into flowerets, reserving stem and stalks for other use.
Cook flowerets in 1-inch of water in large saucepan, covered, over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Meanwhile, heat oil mixture.
Drain broccoli.
Place on plate.
Pour hot oil over. Toss to combine.
Makes 4 servings.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in
cup

water to which 1 teaspoon sugar is
added.
Scald

and add 1/2 cup sugar, salt and shortening, cool; beat egg and add.
Add 2 cups flour and yeast mixture.

and water and beat. Place in bowl
and

Refrigerate or can be used immediately. Will keep in
refrigerator 1 to 2 weeks.
Roll and cut out rolls, let rise 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 375°.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Put in large bowl the chocolate, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
In pan put sugar, milk and butter; bring to boil.
Boil 10 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Pour over marshmallow mixture. With mixer, beat until smooth and creamy.
Add nuts; pour into buttered pan and cool in refrigerator.
Chow down and enjoy!

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into greased (bottom and sides) deep dish pie plate. Drain peaches well, reserving the liquid.
Place peaches on top of batter.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in jar.
Use 2 level teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter, then coconut.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and then butterscotch chips over.
Pour milk over, then top with nuts. Pat mixture down in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until brown.
Cool in pan, then cut into squares.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and onion in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer as long as time permits.
Stir often to prevent sticking.

title: quik kasserole
directions: Drain the corn and potatoes.
Layer the corn, potatoes, peppers and onions in a baking dish.
Add 1/2 can Manwich. Sprinkle on Mrs. Dash to taste.
Crumble the hamburger over the top.
Spread the rest of the Manwich over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving.

title: homemade potato soup
directions: Slice and boil peeled potatoes.
Mash.
Add milk, water, butter, salt and pepper.
Add onions or leeks (as desired). Heat, don't boil.

title: strawberry banana freezie
directions: Combine orange juice, honey, banana and strawberries in blender.
Cover and whirl on high until smooth.
Add enough ice for thickness and whirl again.

title: heath bar salad
directions: Mix dry pudding and crushed pineapple in bowl.
Mix in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Crush Heath bars and mix 3/4 of this into salad.
Top the salad with the rest.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: party buffalo wings
directions: Combine ingredients for sauce and simmer for 10 minutes or microwave for 1 to 3 minutes, stirring after each minute. (Microwave just until bubbly.)
Arrange chicken wing parts in bottom of cake pan or smaller pan (size depends on amount of chicken).
Pour sauce over chicken and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: taco muffins
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and add in taco seasoning.
Mix refried beans with beef mixture.
Spray muffin tins with Pam. Spread biscuits in muffin tin and spoon in beef and bean mixture. Sprinkle cheese on top of each taco muffin.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: dressing for cabbage
directions: This amount is good for a small amount of coleslaw.
If you need a large amount of cabbage such as 10 pounds, you would need 4 times the amount of ingredients used.
Heat vinegar and sugar until sugar is melted.
Cool and pour over cabbage; mix well. Will keep in refrigerator for a few days.

title: shrimp and ground meat spaghetti
directions: Put white onion and ground meat in a frypan; cook and drain. In a separate pan, saut shrimp. Once shrimp is cooked, add ground meat, tomato sauce, tomato paste, water and seasoning. Add sugar and cook on a medium fire. Boil noodles in a separate pot and drain. Add noodles and meat together; stir and let cool.

title: me-maw's dressing
directions: Wash turkey and dry.
Spread with butter and salt, inside and out.
Put breast in one end of pan and dressing in the other. Cover and bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours. Stick knife in thick part of bird.
Done when tender and no blood comes out.

title: paprika artichoke chicken
directions: Sprinkle breasts liberally with paprika.
Melt 1/2 of butter in skillet over medium heat.
Brown breasts on both sides.
Place chicken in 2-quart casserole and arrange artichoke hearts between pieces.
Add other 1/2 of butter, scraping bottom of skillet to loosen stuck pieces.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Saute until tender.
Sprinkle flour over onions and mushrooms.
Stir in broth, sherry and rosemary.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Use sauce as "dunk" for French bread.

title: pork chops a l'orange
directions: Rub pork chops with mixture of pepper, paprika and Season-all. Brown chops on both sides.
Combine orange juice, sugar, curry powder, cloves and orange peel.
Pour over chops.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
If needed, add small amount of water during simmering.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter. Mix with flour. Add milk. Stir in the ingredients above and put in casserole dish. Cover with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° about 45 minutes, until bubbly and brown.

title: rice krispie chicken
directions: Crush Rice Krispies in blender.
Melt 1 stick of margarine. Take chicken pieces and dip in butter and then in Rice Krispies. Put on a cookie sheet or baking pan.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (time may vary according to size of the chicken pieces).

title: orange sorbet
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a medium bowl until the sugar is thoroughly dissolved. Pour into the ice cream maker and follow directions given for your machine.

title: pudding cookie surprise
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Place plastic wrap on the surface of the pudding. Chill.

title: kraut salad(from 1975 edition)
directions: Do not drain kraut; sprinkle parsley over kraut.
Add sugar and let stand for 1/2 hour.
Add remainder of ingredients; mix well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for 12 hours before use.

title: easy as 1-2-3 sausage balls
directions: Knead all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Use 1 large Bundt cake pan or 2 large pans.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour pan.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and soup.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish; top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mushrooms
directions: Slice mushrooms and chop onion.
In a small pot, melt butter, then add mushrooms and onion. Stir constantly until onion becomes transparent and mushrooms are soft, about 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Goes great with steak!

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: In a medium bowl, whisk together baking mix, milk, egg and sugar until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Heat a heavy skillet or griddle over medium-high heat.
Grease lightly.
Using about 1/4 cup batter for each pancake, pour batter into skillet in shape of a heart and cook until bubbles appear on surface and edges are dry.
Turn and cook until bottom is golden brown.
Place cooked pancakes in a warm oven until ready to serve.
Serve with chocolate syrup or syrup of your choice.
Makes about thirteen 4-inch pancakes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a microwave safe bowl, add all ingredients except nuts. Heat on high for 4 to 5 minutes, or until chips and margarine are melted. Stir until creamy smooth and margarine is mixed well. Stir in nuts. Pour into a lightly greased pan. Chill.

title: brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add cocoa and flour to mixture; beat well.
Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan. Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: low-fat breakfast quiche pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except paprika.
Spray 9 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Add ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until light brown and set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.
Contains 170 calories per serving and 4 gr. fat.

title: vegetable bouquet
directions: Drain first seven ingredients then combine all ingredients. Mix well.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Cook sugar, cinnamon, vanilla, water and butter until mixture spins a thread.
Pour in nuts; stir quickly.
Turn out onto waxed paper.
Separate large clumps.

title: tapioca
directions: Soak tapioca in water for at least 1 hour.
Add milk and cook stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add salt, sugar and eggs (mixed).
Cook, stirring 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Add Cool Whip when completely cool. Jello or fruit may be added along with the Cool Whip.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add cranberry sauce; stir until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate until set.
Serves 6.

title: peanut patties
directions: Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove and beat until creamy.
This will take a while.
Drop by teaspoon on foil.

title: worms in dirt dessert
directions: Crumble the Oreos (I use food processor).
Put half in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the margarine, cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
In a separate bowl, stir together milk and pudding until thick.
Add to Cool Whip mixture.
Pour over Oreo crumbs in pan.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Garnish with gummy worms. Serves 12.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream, stirring by hand.
Pour half of batter into 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Swirl batter and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: pepperoni quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen pumpkin dessert
directions: In 4 cup Wonderlier bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs from cheesecake mix and margarine.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of modular mates container.
Spread softened ice cream over crust. Apply seal.
Freeze while preparing pumpkin cheesecake mixture. In small mixing bowl, combine cheesecake filling mix and milk. Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Spread cheesecake mixture over ice cream layer in modular mates rectangular container. Apply seal; freeze several hours until firm.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix up corn bread mix.
Brown hamburger with onion and vegetables.
Pour corn bread mix over all.
Bake at 300° to 350° until bread is done.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into small cubes; boil in 1/2 pan of water until tender.
Add 1/2 cup milk to potatoes.

title: pink arctic freeze
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add pineapple, sauce, nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter and milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Freeze until firm.
Garnish as desired.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: chopped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with almond slivers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
May reheat in the microwave.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. In large bowl at medium speed, cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
At low speed, beat in flour.
Add evaporated milk; beat until well blended. Bake 1 hour and 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack. Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and put in crock-pot.
Add Velveeta cheese, green chiles and tomatoes, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir often until the cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked apple dumplings
directions: Separate biscuits and cut each in 2 or 3 pieces.
Flatten each piece and wrap around a piece of apple.
Place in buttered pan.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and margarine.
Press in pan or dish.
Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour over graham cracker crumbs and top with cherry pie filling.

title: spicy peach salad
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add 1 cup boiling water, mix.
Add 3/4 cup peach syrup.
Cool.
Add drained, cut up peaches and vinegar. Pour into 4 to 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate.

title: ever-so-easy fruitcake
directions: Preheat
oven
Grease a 9-inch tube pan, line with wax paper and grease again (or use generously greased and floured 10-inch
fluted
tube
pan).
Sift together flour and baking soda, set aside.
In large bowl mix remaining ingredients;
blend in
dry
ingredients.
Pour
into
prepared pan. Bake 1
hour
and 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes
out clean.
Cool
15 minutes.
Turn out of pan, remove wax paper. Garnish, if desired.

title: crawfish gumbo
directions: Make a roux. In large pot, add onion, green onion, bell pepper and celery to roux. Stir until soft. Add 2 quarts water and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Simmer for 1 hour. Add crawfish, parsley and garlic, then simmer for 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: lucille's russian pound cake
directions: Mix by hand the oleo, butter, cream cheese, eggs (beaten one at a time), vanilla, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Place 1/2 batter in a greased and floured angel food cake pan.
Arrange 1 cup of nuts and 1 jar drained cherries on top of batter.
Add more batter and add the rest of nuts and cherries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then at 325° for 45 more minutes.

title: smoked turkey and gouda sandwiches
directions: Combine ingredients. Serve hot or cold with chips of your choice.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Place margarine in mixing bowl to soften.
Then combine sugar, salt, flour and milk in saucepan.
Heat over low temperature until sugar and flour is dissolved.
Do not boil; remove from stove and cool to room temperature in fridge.
When cool, pour liquid over butter and add vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy and of spreading consistency.
Takes long to beat (minutes).
Don't give up.
It's worth the wait!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature. Then mix remaining ingredients. Chill. Serve on Ritz crackers or Wheat Thins.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to directions on package.
Combine with next 5 ingredients.
Toss with oil and red wine vinegar. Serve immediately.

title: carrot-potato gratin
directions: Position rack in top third of oven and preheat to 375 degrees. Spray 9 x 13 glass baking dish with cooking spray.
Bring large pot of salted water to a boil.
Add sliced potatoes and carrots.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Arrange 1/3 of cooked vegetables in bottom of prepared dish.
Sprinkle with 1/3 tsp. salt and generous amount of pepper.
Sprinkle 1/3 of grated cheese over layer.
Repeat, layering with remaining cooked vegetables, salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Pour chicken stock over vegetables.
Dot top with 1/4 cup unsalted butter.

Cover and bake until chicken stock is absorbed and vegetables are tender, about 1 hour. Uncover, and bake until top is golden brown, about 10 minutes more. Let gratin stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving. Serves 8.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk with an electric mixer for approximately 2 minutes.
Fold cool whip into pudding mixture in a 13x9-inch pan.
Place one layer of graham crackers.
Place 1/2 of the pudding mixture on top of graham crackers.
Place a second layer of graham crackers on top of pudding mixtures.
Place a third layer of graham crackers on top of the pudding mixture.
Top everything off with chocolate frosting.
Chill in the refrigerator for 12 hours before serving.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets.
When tender, drain and remove peelings.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over beets and boil about 10 minutes.

Place in sterile quart canning jars, filling jars to about 1-inch from the lip of jar, work out air bubbles and seal. If properly sealed, beets have an indefinite shelf life. Refrigerate after opening.

title: fettuccine with shrimp and bacon
directions: Pre-cook the bacon so that it is nice and crisp, then chop it rather coarsely. Remove the skin and seeds from tomato by placing the whole tomato in boiling water for about 10 seconds then plunging into ice water. After removing the skin cut the tomato in half and scoop out the seeds, then chop. Bring a pot of water to a boil for the fettuccine.
Heat a good sized heavy saute pan or skillet. Add olive oil and butter.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Stir baking soda into buttermilk; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter or margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg; add alternately with buttermilk to egg mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in jam.
Bake at 350° until done.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 10 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put in refrigerator to cool about 1/2 hour.

title: oven-baked beef stew
directions: Slice potatoes.
Place half in a large baking dish.
Brown meat, a few pieces at a time, with onion in oil in a large skillet.
Remove meat and onions as they brown to baking dish. Top with remaining sliced potatoes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water; add ice cream and pineapple.
Stir until most of the ice cream is melted.
Cool in refrigerator until salad is jelled.
Serve.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: coffee cake
directions: Melt butter and mix with sugar, cinnamon and walnuts.
Roll biscuits in mixture and place in Bundt pan about 3/4 of height of pan.
Top with cherries and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: german cole slaw dressing
directions: Shred cabbage, sprinkle with salt and let stand to bring out natural juices of cabbage.
Pour cole slaw dressing over cabbage. Use sparingly.

title: crabmeat artichoke casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Blend flour, salt, pepper and mustard until smooth.
Add milk; cook until thickened.
Add Worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and crabmeat; mix well.
Arrange artichoke hearts on bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with sliced eggs, spoon in crab mixture.
Top with buttered bread crumbs which have been mixed with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cuba libre
directions: In 10 ounce glass, put lime juice and drop rind in glass.
Add rum and 2 cubes of ice.
Fill glass with any cola.
Stir well.

title: olive balls
directions: Cream cheese and butter together until well blended.
Cream in the flour.
Shape about 1 tablespoon of dough around each olive. Seal edges.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: crunchy lemon chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cereal, lemon peel and salt.
Dip chicken in egg white.
Coat with the cereal mixture.
Arrange in a 13 x 9-inch pan which has been sprayed with no stick cooking oil. Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice (thin).
Make a white sauce of the butter, flour, salt and milk.
After white sauce thickens, remove from heat and add the grated cheese.
Place potatoes in casserole dish and cover with hot cheese sauce.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, soda, sugar and salt into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sift it into piles in pan.
Then make 3 holes.
In first hole, add vanilla; in second hole, add vinegar and in third hole, add oil. Pour cold water over whole mixture and mix well with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix butter and cocoa in a pan, but do not boil. Add milk, sugar and vanilla. Stir well and add pecans or walnuts. Spread on chocolate cake.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 30 minutes, covered; uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine cornstarch and water; stir until smooth.
Add to eggs; blend well.
Add pineapple, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a lightly
greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs.
Mix in flour and flavorings well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in stem pan at 350°.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender, add to mashed potatoes. Add beaten egg and blend well.
Add flour until good consistency for pancakes. Heat skillet until hot. Place flour in saucer and add potato mixture to coat.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.

title: premier peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Melt oleo and peanut butter in pan over hot water.
Add other ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together sour cream and pudding.
Blend thoroughly. Chill. Makes a great dip for strawberries and bananas.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg white and water until foamy. Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon into egg mixture. Add pecans. Mix well. Spread on a buttered cookie sheet. Bake at 225° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: To jello, add 1 cup of hot water and 1 cup pineapple juice. Pour sugar over berries.
Add nuts, celery and pineapple.
After jello sets, add other ingredients and chill.

title: self-timing cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon into paper lined muffin pan, 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar; mix in a bowl until light.
Add salt and egg.
Beat until light.
Stir in chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoon onto each cupcake.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, salt and water. Bring to a boil. Add peanuts.
Cook until it boils and peanuts stop popping. Add the soda and mix thoroughly. Pour into a buttered dish or pan. Break into pieces when cool. Store in an airtight container.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Freeze in freezer compartment.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar, salt, juice and lemon rind.
Congeal slightly.
Chill milk until it freezes around edge of refrigerator tray.
Whip until very stiff.
Whip in jello. Spread half of crumbs in a large pan, 13 x 9 1/2-inches is a good size pan.
Pour mixture in pan and spread evenly.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Chill 3 hours or longer.
(Can be kept several days.)
Serves 12.

title: cinnamon roll
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Stir into buttermilk.
Divide dough in half. Roll out each half flat with rolling pin, brush melted butter on rolled out dough.
Sprinkle heavily with cinnamon, then sugar, then roll up dough long ways, lay in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 450°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli several hours or overnight.
Saute onion in butter; stir in flour and add water.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Add cheese and salt; stir until cheese melts.
Add beaten eggs and broccoli; mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish and cover with 4 slices toasted bread crumbs stirred in 1 stick melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: toffee
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Place saltine crackers, salt side up, in pan. Combine sugar and margarine.
Boil approximately 10 minutes, stirring until thick.
Pour over crackers and bake 10 minutes in 300° oven.
Pour chocolate chips over crackers.
May need to put in oven again if chips do not melt.
Refrigerate. Break into pieces.

title: baked beans supreme
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; add to beans.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: mom's kneaded biscuit wedges
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and sugar substitute in a medium bowl, stirring to blend.
Cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead 8 to 10 times.
Divide dough into thirds.
Gently shape each third into a ball.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten each ball into a 1-inch thick circle.
Score each into 4 wedges.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Melt margarine over low heat. Blend in flour and seasonings. Remove from heat; slowly stir in milk.
Mix vegetables in sauce. Turn into a buttered 8 cup casserole.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs in a ring around top; fill center with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Yield 6-8 servings.

title: zucchini crisp
directions: Combine zucchini slices and lemon juice.
Cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Cook 3 minutes longer.
Set aside and add 1/2 cup Pie Crust Mixture.

title: date hermits
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add water, then flour sifted with soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir in dates and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: "carolina pound cake"
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar with electric beaters 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time; continue creaming.
Add flour, milk, salt, baking powder and almond extract.
(Blend well all ingredients.)
Pour into a well-greased, floured tube cake pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
This cake will make twelve servings.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and nuts.
Spread in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: butter pecan banana cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake pulls away from pan.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Unmold and cool on racks.
Top.
