title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Mix together in about a 3-quart casserole dish.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: chicken cacciatore(serves 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Bring to boil.
Add chicken.
Cover; reduce heat to simmer for 30 minutes.
Uncover; simmer 30 more minutes.
Take bay leaves out.
Serve over vermicelli (need 4 cups); 90 calories each 1/2 cup serving. Cacciatore:
159 calories per serving.

title: tex-mex lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 3-quart casserole.
In large skillet over high heat, brown beef with scallions for 5 minutes. Discard drippings.
Add chili powder and cumin; cook for 1 minute, stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in corn, tomatoes and beans.
In a bowl, mix Ricotta, eggs and 1 cup of the Monterey Jack.
Line bottom and sides of prepared casserole with 8 of the tortillas; top with 2/3 of the beef mixture.
Cover with Ricotta mixture, remaining tortillas, then remaining beef mixture.
Place in oven. Relax for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle casserole with remaining Monterey Jack; bake for 5 minutes.
Garnish with scallions.

title: linda goldsmith's party chicken
directions: Wrap chicken with bacon.
Cover bottom of greased pan with beef.
Arrange chicken on top of beef in one layer.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: jelly dip
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container in refrigerator. Serve over cream cheese with crackers.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into well-oiled pan.
Set in another pan of warm water.
Bake in moderate oven (400°) until an inserted knife comes out clean.
If desired, additional milk may be added to provide moisture.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese-olive balls
directions: Drain olives and put them on paper towel to dry. Cream cheese and butter. Add flour, baking powder and Tabasco sauce. Roll dough around olives.
Sprinkle with paprika.
(At this point, balls may be put on cookie sheets and frozen. After they freeze, put in freezer bag and freeze for month.
Thaw before baking.)
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.
Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: cool whip pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour. Measure flour.
Add flour and eggs alternately to batter, starting and ending with flour.
Fold in flavorings and whipped topping. Mix only until blended.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Two loaf pans can be used.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: dilled potato salad(low cholesterol)
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain and cool.
Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, onions, salt and dill weed.
Mix well.
Add potatoes and toss gently.
Chill before serving.

title: cola roast
directions: Combine salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Rub over roast. Brown roast on all sides in vegetable oil in Dutch oven.
Drain off drippings.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meat. Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours or until tender.

title: seafood and rice
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Do not boil. Add lemon juice and seafood; heat.
Serve over rice.

title: coon hunter's cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beef and pepper rice
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Stir rice, onion and pepper.
Cook, stirring continuously until changes color.
Add water and soup mix.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle dash of soy sauce.
Add pimento.
Mix in with fork.
Turn heat off.
Cover pot and let set for a few minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat.
Season.
Stir in combined barbecue sauce, pineapple juice, vinegar and cornstarch.
Cover.
Let simmer 35 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks and green pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: yum(spicy seafood salad)
directions: Clean squid and slice into strips 1 inch wide.
If using fresh oysters, remove from shell.
Clean and devein shrimp.
Slice lemon grass and green onion into very thin pieces.
Cut tomatoes into 6 pieces each.
Slice onion.
Place water in a saucepan and boil.
Add shrimp, oyster and squid.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove and drain all water leaving seafood in pan.
Place all other ingredients in pan.
Stir until all ingredients are well mixed.
Place on serving plate covered with lettuce leaves.
Serve 2.

title: baked fruit curry
directions: Drain and dry fruit and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Melt butter; add sugar and spices.
Pour over fruit.
Garnish with cherries.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spicy marinated shrimp(snack on this refreshing starter or serve as a meal!)
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add shrimp, turn off the heat and allow the shrimp to steep for 2 to 3 minutes until pink. Do not boil the shrimp or they will be tough. Transfer to a bowl of ice water to prevent over cooking. In a separate bowl, whisk together the oil and the next 6 ingredients. Season with salt and pepper. Drain shrimp. Pour the marinade over shrimp and toss to coat. Layer shrimp with lemon and onion slices in a large glass bowl. Pour any remaining marinade over the shrimp and refrigerate for at least 4 hours. Can be prepared 1 day ahead.

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring the 5 cups of water to a boil.
Add tea bags, cinnamon and cloves; remove from heat and let steep for 5 minutes.
Mix in a small pan the orange juice, sugar and lemon juice; heat.
Remove tea bags and add juice mixture.
Pour into a tea pot and enjoy.

title: treasure chest bars
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Add brown sugar, sugar and butter or margarine.
Cream these ingredients thoroughly; blend in eggs.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Now add dry ingredients alternately with milk; begin and end with dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in nuts, chocolate bits and cherries.
Turn into 13 x 9-inch or two 8 x 8-inch pans, greased and floured on bottom and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost warm.
Cool to serve.
Cut into squares.

title: tangy red potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/4-inch slices; combine Worcestershire sauce with melted butter and brush on potato slices.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Broil on rack 3-inches from heat 3 to 4 minutes on each side.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, then vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature and mix together with pastry blender or mixer at low speed.
When smooth, add onion, Worcestershire sauce and monosodium glutamate.
Mix well. Shape into a ball, roll in pecans and parsley.
Chill overnight.
To serve, surround with collar of greens interspersed with cranberries.

title: surprise rice and gravy
directions: Cut the chicken and roast beef.
Stir it; put in rice.
Add some bread and cook for a while.
Yum!

title: yellow squash relish
directions: Cube vegetables.
Mix first 6 ingredients and let stand 1 hour, then drain.
Mix remainder of ingredients in pan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes, then add vegetables to this mixture and bring to a boil and pack in jars and seal.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt the oleo, cocoa and water. Bring to a boil. Add the sugar, flour, salt, soda and vanilla. Mix the eggs and sour cream. Add all ingredients and mix well. Bake in large 9 x 13 cake pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Pour icing over cake at once.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and green peppers slowly in Crisco until mixture falls apart.
Add rice, tomatoes and seasonings.
Arrange in large casserole; cover and bake in moderate oven (375°) for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly cream shortening and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add egg and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir together 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Spread in greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Top with berries.

title: hash
directions: Cook stew meat well; tear apart.
Mix all other ingredients together; cook for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add meat while cooking; let simmer.

title: orange soda salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Beat cream cheese until it is fluffy.	Slowly add gelatin that has been dissolved in hot water.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Finely chop all ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in glass jars up to two weeks in refrigerator.

title: makin sausage
directions: After grinding meat, mix other ingredients in, using a wooden spoon.
It's best to sprinkle a little at a time, and continue stirring.
Work down into patties by pinching off a small amount and rolling it around in the palm of your hand.
Flatten by pressing the 2 hands together.
Have hands wet with water for better results.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until it is a little soupy (not too soupy - thick soupy).
Pour into hot black iron pan.
Cook on 450° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: texican squash
directions: Slice squash 1/4 inch thick.
Place squash and onions in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High 9 to 10 minutes, stirring once.
Add chilies (including liquid), jalapenos, cheese and sour cream; toss gently so squash will not be mashed.
Spread half of crushed chips on bottom of a 2-quart rectangular dish. Pour squash mixture in dish and sprinkle with remaining chips. Dust with paprika.
Microwave on 70% power (Medium-high) 10 minutes or until heated through, rotating dish once.

title: ballymaloe irish stew
directions: Heat drippings in a heavy kettle and brown meat.
Add carrots, onions, pepper and beef broth.
Peel potatoes and place on top. Simmer gently, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Transfer meat and vegetables to large bowl with slotted spoon.
Skim fat from stock.
Swirl in butter, parsley and chives and ladle sauce over the meat and vegetables.
Serve with dark beer and brown bread.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef until done; drain.
Add taco sauce and water according to directions and simmer.
Mix all ingredients together for salad.
If salad is refrigerated, it is better to add Fritos, meat and dressing as it is eaten to keep from getting soggy.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Cook cocoa and cornstarch with water until smooth.
Add butter, sugar and salt.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla.

title: quick and easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine mixed vegetables and cream of chicken soup.
Add chicken to mixture.
Place one pie crust in the bottom of a casserole dish (about the same size as the pie crust).
Pour mixture over crust.
Place the other pie crust on top.
Cook at 375° until crust turns brown.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix all together and put in a baked pie shell.
Makes two 9-inch pies.
Chill.

title: "mary catalano's" pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Set pie shells and gelatin mixture aside.
Separate eggs, putting whites in a large bowl; set aside.
Put yolks into saucepan.
While beating yolks with electric hand mixer, add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly so that bottom does not burn.
Add gelatin mix.
Stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Set mixture aside to cool completely.
(You can put this in fridge to hurry the process.)
When cooked pumpkin mixture is completely cool to the touch, continue.

title: peanut butter candy cake
directions: Scald the milk.
Mix with 2 teaspoons butter.
Let cool.
In a large bowl beat 4 eggs.
Add the sugar and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix together flour and baking powder.
Add the flour mixture to the large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Add the milk.
(Makes a thin batter.)
Grease and flour a jellyroll pan.
Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread peanut butter on hot cake.
Chill at least 2 hours (overnight is best).
Melt 2 Hershey bars and spread on cold cake.
Refrigerate to harden chocolate. When you want to cut the cake, let stand out for 20 to 30 minutes, or the chocolate will crack.

title: zesty barbecue sauce(microwave)
directions: Place oil and onion in 1-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 3 cups.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Spread 2/3 of crackers over asparagus in baking dish.
Mix reserved liquid with soup and spread over mixture.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Top with sliced, boiled eggs and serve.

title: million dollar cake
directions: Beat all together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: granny miller's chili
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain off excess grease.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Turn on low and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: indian tawah
directions: Cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Fry onions in grease.
Brown flour in some grease.
Chop onions; add to browned flour.
Put in tomatoes; last, add the meat.
Simmer until tender.

title: drop noodle cookies
directions: Melt chips. Add nuts and noodles. Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper and let cool. Store in cool place. Makes 3 1/2 doz.

title: crock-pot soup
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 12 to 24 hours or on high 4 to 6 hours.

title: anisette biscotti
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Mix eggs, milk, anise and vanilla.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Make three loaves and place on greased cookie sheet or large baking pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes.
Cut loaves in 1-inch slices and return to oven for toasting, about 10 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine milk and eggs and beat together.
Take chicken fillets and dip into egg and milk batter, then roll in bread crumbs.
Pour oil into frying pan and brown both sides of chicken.
Place into shallow baking dish and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: good chili
directions: Cook the ground beef in skillet until it starts to brown. Drain.
Add beans, tomatoes and onions.
Add chili powder and salt to beef mixture and stir.
Put lid on and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugars, vanilla, water and eggs.
Stir until creamy.
Add dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Add chocolate chips and nuts (optional).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oh-so-easy pie
directions: Bring water and oil to a boil.
Pour over flour (flour and salt mixture, if using all-purpose flour).
Mix and pour into pie pan. Mash into place to cover pie pan completely.
Bake at 350° for baked pie shell recipe.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix
all ingredients and bake at 250° for approximately 1 hour.
Stir
occasionally.
Milk
or
cream may be added if dish seems too dry.

title: easy chop suey
directions: Melt shortening; saute meat 8 to 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients, except cornstarch and water.
Stir the water and cornstarch together and pour over to thicken.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: harriet's lamb roll
directions: Place meat on rack on a roasting pan.
Combine all ingredients; spread over roast.
Let stand at least one hour.

title: new orleans squash casserole
directions: Brown beef with salt and pepper.
Drain off grease.
Boil squash and drain.
Beat eggs and cream together.
Mix egg mixture with squash.
Stir in meat and onions.
Add sour cream and water chestnuts.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese to mixture.
Put in large casserole dish in layers:
meat, then cheese.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rice with tomatoes(risotto con pomodoro)
directions: In large skillet saute
green pepper, onion, garlic and basil in heated olive oil.
Saute until all peppers are tender but not brown.
Stir
in
rice,
tomatoes, salt, pepper, water and bouillon cubes.
Cook covered over
low
heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: baked ham
directions: Place ham in pan.
Put pineapple all over it.
Add sugar over top.
Pour pineapple juice over that.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Grease another large bowl. Place dough in the large bowl, turning dough once to grease the top.
Cover lightly with foil and let stand overnight (or all day) in a warm place.
After 8 to 12 hours, punch down and knead lightly, then divide dough into 3 parts and knead 8 to 10 times. Place in greased loaf pans.
Lightly cover with foil and let rise all day (or night).
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: homestyle tuna pot pie
directions: Combine tuna, peas and carrots, onions and potato or mushroom soup. Add milk and poultry seasoning. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into crust. Top with other crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: basque bean salad
directions: Cut broccoli into 1-inch florets; slice stems into strips. Blanch broccoli in boiling water for 1 minute.
Rinse in cold water; drain.
In serving bowl, combine broccoli, beans, celery and onion; mix well.
In small jar with lid, combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard; shake well.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Toss gently until well coated.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Sprinkle top with bacon just before serving.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Cut 2 large pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil; place a chicken breast in center of each.
Top with onion and remaining ingredients.
Wrap well; place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 servings, 221 calories and 1/8 grams of fat per serving.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all except dressing and Fritos.
Chill.
Just before serving, add dressing and Fritos.

title: beef and gravy
directions: Place meat, onion soup mix, celery soup and water in baking dish; stir well.
Cover and place in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Stir occasionally.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and add egg until blended.
Add flour mixture to first batter until just blended.
Add chips and drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Or make into balls and flatten with fork.
Could be rolled in powdered sugar.

title: * depression cake *
directions: Stew raisins in water until only 1 cup of liquid remains; cool.
Cream sugar, shortening and liquid.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves and a pinch of salt, which have been sifted together.
Add raisins last.
Bake in greased loaf pan in moderate oven.
Frost with caramel icing, if desired.

title: lemon pecan bread
directions: Cream butter. Gradually add sugar, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well. Combine dry ingredients. Add alternately with buttermilk. Stir in pecans and lemon rind.
Pour into a loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: becky's fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch bits in top of double boiler. Add Chinese noodles and nuts.
Put into 8-inch lightly buttered pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: good stuff marinade
directions: Mix well; pour over meat.
Let sit from 4 to 24 hours.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Stir all together. Serve with bread or chips.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all together.
Can bake 20 minutes at 350° or serve cold.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Salt and cook enough turnips to make six cups of mashed turnips; drain and mash.
Add softened cream cheese, sugar and margarine and mix well.
Pour into casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly hot and lightly browned.

title: broccoli and spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook and drain broccoli and spinach. Saute onion in butter.
Mix together broccoli, spinach, sauteed onion, mushroom soup, eggs, water chestnuts and corn flakes.
Put into casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Add onion rings on top and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: two-way baked potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes.
When cool, peel and slice.
Place potatoes in shallow baking dish.
Pour 1/4 to
1/2 cup bourbon over
and butter generously.
Cover with lots
of
dark
brown sugar.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.	Great
at Thanksgiving or any time.

title: leslie's crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and onion.
Spread in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with cocktail sauce.
Top cocktail sauce with crab meat.
Garnish with paprika and lemon wedges.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: snicker bar ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Mix thoroughly with mixer.
Add cut up Snicker bars and Eagle Brand milk to mixture.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into freezer can and add enough milk to reach fill line on the can.
Stir thoroughly. Freeze according to freezer directions.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump pineapple and juice in pan evenly.
Then dump pie filling in and spread with spoon.
Next sprinkle cake mix evenly over filling.
Slice butter evenly over top and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: frontier dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions. Drain.
In saucepan, combine the chili and soup.
Put the macaroni back in the pan with the soup and chili. Simmer until hot.
You've got a one pot meal for 6!

title: crab puffs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and add flour.
Stir quickly until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a smooth ball.
Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, beating with a wooden spoon after each addition.
Beat well until smooth.
Add crab mixture and stir well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake another 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble, then drain.	Prepare 9-inch pie
shell.
Mix
cheese
and sausage.
Sprinkle in pie shell. Lightly beat eggs in bowl.	Combine remaining ingredients and add to	egg mixture.
Pour into shell.	Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.	Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken and cut in serving size pieces.
Season chicken pieces with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Roll each piece in flour and place on a cookie sheet, skin side up. Sprinkle with oil.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: rigatoni alla vodka with shrimp
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Cook onion, garlic and basil until soft (medium heat, 8 to 10 minutes).
Add vodka.
Raise heat to boil.
Stir frequently.
Simmer until 1/4 of mixture evaporates and vodka aroma subsides.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Mix together all ingredients and heat until the cheeses are melted.
Dip cubed Italian bread in the heated fondue.

title: glazed strawberry gelatin pie
directions: Prepare pie filling as directed on package for pie.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Chill 1 hour.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Add berries and spoon carefully over pie filling.
Chill until firm, at least 3 hours.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Place berries in baking dish.
Mix other 3 ingredients until crumbly.
Spread over berries.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: Dip steak in flour; sprinkle with salt and pepper and brown in a little shortening.
After it browns, remove steak.
Put some flour in excess shortening and stir good.
Brown to make gravy.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and flour.
Work together like pie dough, then add
lemon
rind
and lemon juice, milk and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites last and fold in.
Makes enough for one crust.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together, place in buttered baking dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: rosie's fruit salad
directions: Dice all fruit.
Cut grapes in half.
Combine all fruit and pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: baby almond cheesecakes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line 24 mini muffin cups with mini paper cupcake liners.
In food processor or with electric mixer, beat cream cheese with almond paste until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, except jelly and berries; beat until smooth.
Divide among muffin cups and bake 15 minutes.
Remove from tins; cool slightly and chill.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding, powdered sugar and milk with mixer; fold in Cool Whip.

In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer graham crackers on the bottom followed by 1/3 of pudding mixture, graham crackers again, then 1/3 of pudding mixture until there are three layers of each with pudding on top.
Stir Milnot, cocoa, melted butter, sugar and flour in small saucepan.
Heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool and pour over pudding.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour over crust and cool.
Blend jello and hot water. Add cold water and strawberries.
Pour over creamy mixture.
Chill until set.

title: best beans you'll ever eat
directions: Mix all the ingredients and cook slowly.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cinnamon with sugar and salt.
Mix ingredients in order. Pour into 9-inch pie shells.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then reduce temperature to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer or until done in center.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, butter, milk and peanut butter and hard boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add the oats, cocoa and vanilla. Spoon onto tinfoil and cool, then eat.

title: sweet and sour pork meatballs
directions: Combine pork, garlic, onion, egg, Panko, soy sauce and pepper; mix well.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on roasting rack in baking pan or on broiler pan.
Bake, uncovered, in 450° oven for 25 minutes, or until browned.
Turn into serving bowl.
Pour sweet and sour sauce over all.
Gently toss to coat.
Serve with wooden picks as appetizers or with hot, cooked rice as a main dish. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: firehouse meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour 12 ounces tomato sauce over meat and reserve remainder.
Add cracker, onions, egg, salt and pepper. Combine until uniform.
Pack meat into a large loaf pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over the loaf.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until loaf is firm and pulls away from sides of the pan. Remove from oven and allow to cool 10 minutes.
Pour off grease and reserve for gravy.
Pour hot fat in skillet and fry 1 chopped onion.
Add 1/2 teaspoon Season-All and 4 heaping tablespoonfuls flour to skillet.
Pour in enough water to make a medium thick gravy.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs and milk; add sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour over bread; let set 5 minutes.
Add pie filling to bread mixture. Pour into a lightly greased pan; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Set in a larger pan, 1/2 full of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Toast bread.
Crumb bread in blender.
Combine all dry ingredients together with the bread crumbs.
Soak chicken parts in milk, using all the milk; then roll chicken pieces in the crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a nonstick baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes; turn pieces once and bake 30 additional minutes.

title: raspberry topped lemon velvet
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 2 cups of boiling water, add marshmallows and stir until almost completely dissolved.
Blend mayonnaise, cream cheese and 1/2 of jello until smooth.
Stir in remaining jello and chill until thick and syrup like.
Fold in pineapple.
Mix whipped topping with milk and vanilla and fold into jello.
Pour into lightly oiled 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish, chill until set.
Meanwhile, dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup of boiling water, stir in cold water, chill until thick and syrup like.
Spoon raspberry jello over top of first layer and chill until set.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Can use crumbled bacon, browned and drained, and a little onion.

title: cookie candy
directions: Combine and boil together the margarine, sugar and milk for 1 minute.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Add oatmeal, cocoa and salt; stir until well mixed and drop by spoonfuls on a flat surface.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook all together until warm.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together in a large saucepan.
Add desired color and amount of food coloring.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Turn out onto floured wax paper.
Knead until stickiness is gone.
Does wonders with a group of kids on a rainy day.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix, but do not cook all above ingredients.
Scrub cucumbers, leaving peel on.
Slice thin or dice.
Dice onions and green peppers.
Put cucumbers, onions and peppers in containers and pour juice over and freeze.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in salt water (enough to cover chicken).
When done, remove chicken and debone; set aside.
Reserve broth for dumplings.

title: pasta with crab meat
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain.
Add chopped tomatoes and green peppers.
Add crab meat.
Stir in jar of Ranch dressing.
Season to taste.

title: green chile burritos number 2
directions: Brown diced meat in fat in a large, heavy skillet or saucepan. Add onion, green chiles, cut in quarters with their juices and drained tomatoes.
Add enough water to cover, then add salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook, covered, until meat is very tender.
Mix cornstarch or flour with small amount of water to form a thin paste and add to mixture to thicken slightly.
Heat large flour tortillas on a griddle and fill with meat mixture; fold.
Eat and enjoy.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut
meat
into thin strips. In skillet heat shortening and brown
meat, turning frequently. Stir in onion soup and 2 cups water.
Cover
and	simmer	30 minutes. Stir in peppers. Simmer, covered,
minutes
or until meat is tender. Blend cornstarch with
cup
water.
Stir
into skillet.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.	Serve over rice or noodles.

title: nantucket cranberry pie
directions: Butter 10-inch pie plate.
Chop cranberries and nuts; add 1/2 cup sugar.
Place in pie pan.
Mix together eggs, butter, 1 cup sugar, flour and almond extract.
Pour over berry-nut mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oven baked barbecued chicken
directions: Heat a small amount of oil in a large skillet, fry chicken until browned, drain and place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, saute onions in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken, bake at 350° about 1 hour or until chicken is done. Baste.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Use hand whip.
Cream together salad dressing and sugar.
Add water and vanilla to creamed mixture; mix well.
Add flour, soda, cocoa and salt; mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: green bean salad
directions: Cook green beans, then cool and drain. Blend all other ingredients (except bacon) and pour over beans.
Fry bacon crispy; break into small bits and stir into beans. Sprinkle dried Durkee onions on top.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and lard together coarsely. Add remaining ingredients, blending well. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well.
Beat eggs.
Add vinegar.
Put in 1 cup measuring cup; fill with water to make 1 cup.
Add to flour and lard mixture.
Keeps one week in refrigerator and freezer.
Makes 5 double crusts.

title: quicky casserole
directions: Layer ingredients as listed.
Bake at 350°.
When it bubbles, remove from the oven and put a can of refrigerator biscuits (baked according to directions) on top of casserole.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Combine eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: whole wheat snickerdoodles
directions: Cream until fluffy the sugar, butter and egg.
Mix flour (both kinds), soda and salt.
Then add to creamed mixture.
Chill.
Shape into balls.
Roll in 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon, mixed together.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 45 minutes, depending on your oven.

title: fruit salad
directions: Make Jell-O with hot water and put in refrigerator until thick.
Fold in remaining ingredients and put in refrigerator until firm.

title: letter pretzels(fun snack for children!)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add honey, salt and flour; knead.
Roll pieces and form letters from the pieces.
Brush letters with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.
Enjoy!

title: sunset chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish with 1 ounce slice of Swiss cheese on each breast.
Mix 2 cans of soup with wine or vermouth and chicken broth and pour over meat.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Melt butter and add stuffing mix.
Remove foil and add stuffing mix on top.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: halloween spiders
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a glass bowl in microwave for approximately 2 minutes at power level 7.
When completely melted, stir in noodles and mix. Drop small mounds on a cookie sheet covered with wax paper. Refrigerate until hard.

title: michelle's vegetable dip
directions: Combine sugar, water, vinegar and salad dressing mix; stir and refrigerate 2 hours.
Add mayonnaise.
Yield:
1 cup.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer on low heat 2 hours.
Serve warm.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Combine the last 3 ingredients and heat until cheese melts. Pour over potatoes.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fresh fruit pie(may use pears, apples, peaches, etc.)
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Spread fruit in bottom of dish and arrange bread cubes over fruit.
Melt margarine with sugar. Cool and add the beaten egg.
Pour over bread.

title: sweet 'n sour baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes or until bubbly around edges.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix filling in large mixing bowl. Pour a little filling in bottom of Pyrex baking dish. Layer wafers, bananas and filling alternately to top, ending with filling. Extra whipped topping may be used on top.

title: alfred's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and cream cheese.
Mix sugar, then eggs.
Add flour, salt and then vanilla.
Start in cool oven at 275° for 45 minutes, then at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: cucumbers on rye bread
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise and dressing; spread on rye bread. Place one cucumber slice on top of each slice of bread.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Chill and serve.

title: frozanne frosting
directions: In large bowl, mix together butter, salt, vanilla and about 1/3 of the supreme powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Alternately add remaining sugar and milk, beating until smooth and of spreading consistency.
Stir in chocolate decorettes, reserving some for garnish.
Frosts two 8 or 9-inch cake layers or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake.

title: mexican appetizer rolls
directions: On a flat serving plate:

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend margarine into flour and powdered sugar with pastry blender or 2 knives.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Stir together pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar. Press onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes and then cool.
Combine the cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar. Mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over pretzel crust and then chill.

title: south haven cheese potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in small pan.
Add onions and saute.
In large bowl, mix potatoes, onions, oleo, soup, sour cream and Cheddar cheese. Set some cheese aside for top.
Mix.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Toss; set aside cheese over top.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven. (I spray pan with Pam before putting in potato mixture.)

title: peter rabbit casserole
directions: Cook onion and carrots in water, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole 45 minutes at 350°.

title: doughnuts
directions: Heat oil.
Take biscuits from can.
Make hole in center of each biscuit.
Drop in oil.
When they turn brown, take out and roll in sugar.
Serve.

title: watermelon fruit bowl
directions: Into a large bowl, dissolve gelatin with boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Refrigerate until thickened but not set.
Stir in fruit (any combination).
Any other flavor gelatin could be used, also.

title: pan roasted potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes 10 minutes; drain.
Arrange in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour margarine over potatoes, sprinkle all sides with salt, pepper and paprika.
Turn 2 or 3 times while baking.
Bake in 325° oven 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Baste before serving.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare 10-inch pie pastry; do not bake. In skillet, cook and stir ground beef until brown.
Drain; stir in salt, oregano, pepper, onion, crumbs, 1/2 cup tomato sauce and green pepper.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Spread cheese evenly over filling.
Cover edge with strips of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning; remove it the last 15 minutes.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Stir remaining tomato and chili sauce and serve with pie.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk blending thoroughly.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture, adding Heath pieces.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: fun snack mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 10 1/2 cups snack.

title: carrot soup
directions: Boil together the onion, carrots, broth, water and nutmeg. Simmer, covered, until carrots are tender.
Cool enough to puree in blender.
Puree until carrot mixture is smooth.
Add peanut butter while pureeing.
Pour into saucepan and stir in cream. Reheat soup, stirring often and serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: lemonade kicker
directions: Fill a tall glass with ice. Then add vodka, blue curaco, and sour mix. Fill to top with soda. Garnish with lemon slice.

title: my favorite hot rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir until shortening is melted.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add dissolved yeast.
Add egg and mix well.
Add flour to make soft dough. Cover tightly and put in refrigerator until ready to use.
When ready to use, punch down.
Shape into balls and put in a pan or cookie sheet.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake in a 375° or 400° oven for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: crab souffle
directions: Day Before:
Dice 4 slices of the bread and place in buttered 3-quart size Pyrex shallow baking dish.
Mix together in bowl crab, mayonnaise, onion, celery, green pepper, parsley, lemon peel, salt and pepper.
Place this mixture in dish over the diced bread.
Cover mixture with remaining whole slices of bread (or half slices) to cover mixture completely.

title: salmon patties
directions: Break up salmon in large bowl.
Add potatoes, onions, parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Form into patties.
Coat patties with flour.
Dip into beaten egg and then roll in bread crumbs. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: nut cookie crust
directions: Mix margarine and brown sugar in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until crumbly.
Press mixture against bottom and side of ungreased pie pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inches, building up 1/2-inch edge; flute edge, if desired.

title: oven fried chicken chimichangas
directions: Wrap tortillas in damp paper towels; microwave for 15 seconds. Brush tortillas with vegetable oil (keep tortillas warm). Combine chicken, cheese and onions.
Place chicken mixture in center of tortillas.
Fold left and right sides toward center. Fold up bottom and top; secure with toothpick.
Place in lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, or until crisp.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Sift salt, baking powder and flour; add to mixture.
Chill 1 hour, roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza #2
directions: Flatten rolls and bake according to directions.
Mix next 3 ingredients together.
Cool rolls.
Spread dressing mix on top of rolls; add chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.

title: frozen strawberry meringue
directions: In the large bowl of an electric mixer, beat egg whites on medium speed until they hold soft moist peaks.
Add sugar, about 1 tablespoon at a time, and beating constantly until meringue is thick and glossy.
Add 1 cup of crushed strawberries.
Beat on medium speed just to blend.
Transfer meringue mixture to a freezer container.
Cover well.
Freeze at least 1 hour until solid.
Serve and put berries on top.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Boil water. Thoroughly dissolve orange jello and tapioca pudding in water (the tapioca will tend to settle and clump if not stirred completely). Refrigerate until partially set (2 to 3 hours). Thaw Cool Whip and stir into partly set jello until it is mixed and smooth. Stir in oranges and refrigerate until ready to serve. Also good with raspberries and raspberry jello or strawberries and strawberry jello, etc.

title: tangy meatballs
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients, shape into approximately 20 to 25 meatballs.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add chili sauce and grape jelly in a slow cooker. Mix together and add meatballs.
Cook on low to warm through.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 1-quart baking dish or 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Arrange slices in dish.
Mix half of the brown sugar with cinnamon and nutmeg; sprinkle over apples.
Add juices and zest.

title: joe's camp coffee (liqueur)waterford, michigan
directions: Combine water, sugar and coffee in a pan and bring to a full boil.
Skim the top and cool.
Pour into a container.
Add vodka, coffee beans and vanilla beans.
Store in a cool dark place for 3 weeks. Strain.
Ready to serve.
Pour into a 1 qt. mason jar and drink from jar.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening and add milk.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Roll dough into 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread sausage over dough.
Roll dough into jelly roll.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Slice dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice and cool.
Add the Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Add the fruit all together.
Put in refrigerator and let set for about 1 hour or two.

title: potato casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, combine ingredients, folding all into potatoes.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; cool. Add pineapple, 7-Up, marshmallows and bananas. Chill until firm. Mix flour and sugar; add egg, then pineapple juice. Cook, stirring constantly. Take from heat and add butter. When cool, add cream, whipped. (Dream Whip may be used.) Spread on gelatin layer.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a pastry shell; turn oven to 350°.
Bake in hot oven 10 minutes, then reduce heat and bake for 50 minutes or until brown and firm.

title: orange icebox cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars.
Add egg and beat.
Add juice and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda; then peel and pecans.
Shape into two 1 1/4 rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper. Chill until firm. Slice 3/16-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 375° for 8 or 9 minutes.

title: friendship tea(russian tea)
directions: Mix together and store covered.
Mix 1 to 2 teaspoons with a cup of hot water.
Delicious!

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the pineapple, lemon juice and box of pudding.
Add oranges, fruit cocktail and the bananas, diced.

title: potato salad with a twist
directions: Boil potatoes after cutting in wedges, leaving skins on; drain when soft.
In large bowl, add Italian dressing to potatoes with celery seed, dill and sugar.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Add Kraft salad dressing and heat in microwave until warm.
Serve warm.

title: potato casserole(lighter eating - 3 points per cup)
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam. Combine all ingredients and place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and onions together and place in a wide-mouth gallon jar.
Mix all other ingredients together and heat to boiling, making sure that all sugar dissolves. Pour mixture over the cucumbers and onions. Let cool and store in refrigerator.

title: apple brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Blend well.
Makes a thick batter.
Add diced apples and stir.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and spread around.
Bake 1 hour.

title: tammy's cole slaw
directions: Mix flavor package from Ramen noodles, oil and vinegar; set aside.
Mix cabbage, sugar, salt, pepper, almonds and sunflower seeds; mix in vinegar and spices mixture.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Just before serving, crush noodles and mix with cabbage.

title: no name chicken
directions: Heat together all ingredients.
Place in casserole.
layer of chicken mixture, layer of flour tortillas (cut in quarters) and layer of chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked apple cake
directions: Soak raisins in hot water.
Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Gradually add sugar to eggs and continue to beat until mixture is pale in color and thick in texture.
Do not underbeat.
Drain raisins.
Add water and vanilla to egg mixture.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Add apples and raisins.
Pour batter into a 9-inch square pan, sprayed with nonstick spray. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 9 servings.

title: manicotti with meat
directions: Saute ground beef and onion.
Drain off excess drippings and add rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour 1/2 jar of spaghetti sauce in baking pan.
Cook manicotti noodles, drain and stuff with meat mixture.
Place in baking dish with sauce.
Pour the rest of the sauce over the top of the noodles and spread extra cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Whip Miracle Whip salad dressing and Cool Whip to make dressing. Combine apples, marshmallows, celery and walnuts. Add enough salad dressing to moisten. Chill. Add apple slices before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, then roll into balls and then put meatballs in a pan of water.
Let boil for about 20 minutes, then drain and put meatballs in crock-pot and pour spaghetti sauce over them and let cook all day.

title: lobster bisque
directions: Wash lobster tails.
Parboil lobster tails by dropping in boiling chicken broth for 2 minutes.
Douse in cold water to cool. Cut membrane on underside of shell and remove meat.
Put empty shells back in broth.
Cut lobster meat into bite sized pieces, sprinkle with Madeira and set aside.
Add carrots, onions, bay leaf, marjoram and wine to broth and shells.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Line a colander with layers of cheesecloth.
Place over a bowl and strain mixture through it.
Let stand for a few minutes to get all liquid.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Stir in flour; mix until smooth.
Add lobster broth, milk and tomato paste.
Simmer about 10 minutes, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat; add lobster meat, heavy cream, salt and coarse pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: punch - "good"
directions: *Flavor of jello determines color of punch you want. Strawberry or cherry is red, lemon is yellow, lime is green; add food coloring for desired color.

title: quaker chocolate-oat chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well. Stir in oats, chips and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375°.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: hot sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes and onions.
Puree 1 tomato and peppers in blender.
In a bowl, mix all ingredients.
Add salt to taste.

title: wagon wheel cobbler
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening.
Add 1/4 cup water and mix. Roll this as a pie crust.
Spread mixture of 3/4 cup sugar and 1 stick margarine (softened) on the crust.
Roll like a jelly roll and cut into 1-inch thick crossways.
Lay flat in a 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Put sugar,
milk and margarine in pan; mix and bring to hard boil.
Let
boil for one minute then remove from heat and quickly add remaining ingredients.
Stir together and drop on waxed paper. Allow to set and enjoy.

title: crust for peach cobbler
directions: Add enough cold water to moisten and make it easy to work with.

title: john davidson's turtle brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup milk on top of double boiler. Stir until caramels melt.
Combine cake mix, remaining milk and margarine.
Blend until mixture holds together.
Stir in nuts. Press 1/2 of mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top and pour caramel mixture over them.
Crumble remaining cake mixture on top of caramel and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool slightly and cut into bars.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Crumble Bleu cheese; set aside some for garnish.
In mixing bowl, combine cheese with the rest of the ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese. Store in an airtight container in refrigerator.
It will keep indefinitely and the recipe may be doubled.

title: "chicken special"
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in bottom of roasting pan.
Place chicken on top, then sprinkle onion soup mix over all.
Cover tightly.
Do not take cover off until done.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together and beat well.
Bake in 3 9-inch round layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat to boil chicken, 1 onion, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat and
simmer
for 30 minutes or until fork-tender.
Save 3 1/2 cups of
chicken
broth
cups
if
not using sherry). Remove meat in large pieces, discarding bones and skin.
Cook spaghetti as label
directs.
Drain
and
place	in a greased baking dish.

title: hickory smoked brisket
directions: Place brisket in large piece of foil or in cooking foil. If too big for crock-pot, cut in half and stack. Sprinkle generously with liquid smoke and celery, onion and garlic salt. Wrap well and put into crock-pot and cook for 1 hour on high, then turn to low for 8 to 9 hours. Slice thinly and cover with barbecue sauce.

title: self filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package directions. Fill paper baking cups in muffin pan 2/3 full.
Cream the cheese with the sugar. Beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop 1 rounded teaspoonful of the cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as the package directs.
Makes 30 cupcakes.

title: chocolate macadamia nut pie
directions: Crush or pulverize wafers in food processor.
Combine crumbs with melted butter and press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch pie pan.
Melt chocolate in double boiler over hot, not boiling, water or in microwave.
Allow to cool slightly.
Beat together melted chocolate, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Fold nuts into creamed mixture.
Whip cream until peaks form.
Beat about a fourth of the whipped cream into the cheese mixture, then gently fold in remaining cream.
Pour filling into chocolate crumb crust and freeze at least 4 hours or overnight. Remove 10 minutes before serving.

title: chess cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together with mixer.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Pour cooked potatoes and onions into buttered baking dish. Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes. Bake about 30 minutes.

title: easy san francisco stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add beef; cook and stir until no longer pink.
In small bowl, combine jelly, cornstarch and mustard; blend well.
Add jelly mixture and frozen vegetables to meat.
Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: wacki cake
directions: Sift all dry
ingredients into an ungreased cake pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Make 3
holes in dry mixture.
Into one hole, pour vinegar, into another hole	put
vanilla and the last hole the oil.
Pour water over the entire mixture and mix with a wooden spoon until well blended.
Bake
at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Check for doneness with
toothpick in center of cake.
Makes a very moist chocolate cake.

title: diet peanut butter pie
directions: Make a crust out of the crackers and melted margarine.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: fried cabbage
directions: In a very large skillet, fry the bacon until done. Drain most of the grease off. Place the chopped cabbage with the onion in the skillet with the bacon and cook over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes. Season with the pepper.

title: cathedral window candy
directions: Place butter in 3-quart casserole.
Heat in microwave on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Add chocolate morsels.
Heat in microwave on Medium for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until chocolate is melted.
Cool chocolate enough so that marshmallows won't melt when stirred in.
Add nuts as well.
Allow to stand until stiff enough to form rolls.
Spread coconut on two 1 to 1 1/2 foot each sheets of wax paper.
Divide marshmallow mixture in half.
Form in long rolls on coconut.
Coat all sides of rolls evenly with coconut. Store in refrigerator until firm.
Cut in 1/4 to 1/2 inch slices.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cook onion, bell pepper and celery until tender.
Boil water; then add rice and soup mix after it comes to a second boil.
Then boil
7 minutes longer.
Add sausage, onion, bell pepper and celery to rice.
Simmer for 15 minutes; then bake, covered, for 20 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta with anchovy and onion
directions: Cook pasta to al dente.
Rinse anchovies in lukewarm water and place in milk.
Soak for 1/2 hour.
Saute onion and garlic in oil. Remove anchovies and discard milk.
Dice anchovies and add to pan.
Cook for several minutes until anchovies begin to come apart.
Add spaghetti sauce and cream and mix thoroughly.
Add pepper and cheese.
Serve over pasta.
Serves 4.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine the ingredients and pour into a greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix 2 cups crushed corn flakes with 1/4 cup margarine.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 48 little miracles
directions: Combine peanut butter and sugar; mix well.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Roll into 48 balls.
Place on ungreased pan.
Flatten with floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Allow to cool before removing from cookie sheet.
That's all there is to it. Enjoy.

title: squash au gratin
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water until tender. Crumble bread.
Mix in egg, margarine, salt and pepper.
Bake in dish.
Top with cheese; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: To milk, add lemon juice and baking soda; set aside.
Cream brown sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Mix in sour milk mixture and flour.
Fold in rhubarb and vanilla.
Pour into prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: raisin nut spice squares
directions: Add water to raisins and boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add shortening.
Cool.

title: pillow potato biscuits
directions: Combine potato flakes, oleo, water and sugar and mix well.
Add water and biscuit mix.
Blend all ingredients to a soft dough. (May add more cold water if needed.)
Turn out and work about ten turns.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush tops with milk.
Bake 13 to 14 minutes at 425°.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Cool completely.

title: connie's baked beans
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
To this mixture, add the next 4 ingredients.
Add the garlic salt and catsup.
Top with bacon. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then add stewing meat.
Bake in oven at 350° for 3 to 4 hours until meat is tender.
Cover while baking.
Add water, if necessary.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat over medium heat, stirring to break up, when all red is gone, remove to a dish and cook onions in fat until translucent, while onions cook, lightly beat the eggs and milk with sour cream and caraway seed.
Drain onions and meat well.
Place evenly in pie shell.
Pour the sour cream mixture over meat.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 35 minutes or until pastry is nicely browned and egg sour cream mixture is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: honey-pecan fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving size portions; wash and pat dry.
Pour buttermilk into a large bowl; add chicken pieces.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 1/2 hours.
Mix flour, salt, garlic powder and cayenne pepper.
Drain chicken and dredge through the flour mixture, shaking off excess flour.
Let chicken stand 20 minutes at room temperature.
Melt butter in a heavy small skillet or saucepan over low heat; stir in honey and bring to boil.
Add pecans and simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat 1/2 to 3/4-inch of oil in a large, heavy skillet to 375°.
Add chicken in small batches (do not crowd) and fry until crisp, golden brown and cooked thoroughly (about 7 minutes per side).
Drain on paper towels. Arrange on platter; pour over the chicken the honey-pecan glaze. Serve immediately.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Dump in bowl and stir together.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour in batter and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: mustard slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate and serve on hot dogs.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine.
Heat and simmer.
Use with ribs or any meat on the grill.
A favorite!

title: sea scallops in herb broth(serves 4)
directions: In a medium saucepan combine 1 1/2 cups parsley, 1 cup watercress, shallots, water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Strain; reserve liquid.
Set aside.

title: lasagna for two
directions: Saute
meat
and garlic in oil until brown, drain.
Add tomato sauce,
salt, pepper and oregano.	Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: washable finger paint
directions: Beat ingredients until stiff.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot oil.
Cook until well browned.
Drain on paper towels.

title: canned beets
directions: Wash and cook beets until skin peels off.
Combine remaining ingredients together.
Pack beets in jar, pour liquid to fill jars.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel, core and chop tomatoes.
Cook tomatoes for 1 hour and then add rest of clean chopped vegetables and spices.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 15 minutes and then jar.
Makes about 16 pints.

title: no name crackers
directions: Mix in large container and shake vigorously.

title: sparkling champagne dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Let stand about 10 minutes to cool.
Add champagne.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: no-peek casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly. Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Do not peek.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mother's chocolate cake
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a tube pan. Frost with 7 minute frosting.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and stir, then add half flour (2 1/2 cups).
Mix well.
Add shortening and salt and stir well.
Add remaining flour 1 cup at a time.
Let rise until double in size.
Pinch off and place in greased pan.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mostaccioli and italian sausage
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
Cut sausage links into 1/2-inch pieces and brown in skillet.
Drain grease and add sliced onion and green pepper.
Cover and steam.
Prepare spaghetti sauce according to directions.
Add sausage, onion and green pepper. Set aside.

title: christe's real new orleans seafood gumbo
directions: Crab Directions:
Put crabs in sink; pour a large pot of boiling salty water on them.
When they stop moving they are dead. Remove the point on underside of shell and the top shell.
Clean out the guts and fingers and break crabs in half.
Rinse.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Cut cabbage into fine pieces.
Add onions and carrots.
Heat the ingredients and pour over cabbage.
Put in refrigerator.

title: macaroni-tuna casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onions and green pepper until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup, tuna, olives, mustard, salt, pepper, milk, salad dressing and cooked macaroni. Pour into a buttered lasagne dish; top with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: applesauce stir cake
directions: Beat sugar, oleo and egg.
Add and mix well molasses and applesauce to which the soda has been added.
Blend together the cinnamon, allspice, salt and flour.
Add to the creamed mixture. Blend in the walnuts and raisins.
Spread in the 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs first.
Add sugar, melted margarine, syrup, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until brown.

title: crabbie
directions: Blend softened margarine and cheese spread.
Add garlic powder, seasoned salt, mayonnaise and crabmeat.
Mix well. Spread on split English muffins.
Freeze for at least 30 minutes. Remove from freezer 5 minutes before using.
Cut each round into 6 pie-shaped pieces.
Broil until they puff up and are bubbly and slightly golden brown.
Serve hot.
Yields 48.

title: pudding delight
directions: Make vanilla pudding according to directions on box.
Let set until firm.
Add the large container of Cool Whip and mix until smooth.
Layer the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch container with graham crackers.
Add a layer of pudding mixture next alternating pudding mixture and crackers.
End with a layer of crackers.
Spread chocolate frosting on top.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: dale's delightful ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, condensed and evaporated milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into container and fill to 1 1/2 inches from top with milk.
Yield: 1 1/2 gallons.

title: gladys' peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly; set aside.
Beat egg yolks until fluffy. Combine granulated sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Beat into egg yolks; gradually add hot milk. Mix well.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly until filling is thick and smooth. Add butter and vanilla.
Fill pie crust with peanut butter mixture.
Pour hot custard over peanut butter layer. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Spread over top of pie, sealing edges well.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain water from 2 cans of beans.
Pour into slow cooker. Spread out evenly.
Spread one can of French fried onion rings over that.
Spread 1 can of cream of mushroom over that and cover with a layer of the shredded cheese.
Add the remaining 2 cans of beans, including the water.
Spread remaining can of onion rings and cream of mushroom.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Cook slow for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix oil and eggs together; then add both mixtures together.
Add peanut butter.
Bake at 325° until done.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cookie paint
directions: Stir egg yolk into water.
Put 1/2 teaspoon of egg mixture into 5 teacups.
Add a different color to each teacup to make various colors.
Paint cookies with Q-tips, then bake according to directions.

title: "create a commotion"(sausage and cheese biscuits)
directions: Brown sausage with onions, breaking up sausage into small pieces. Drain and rinse sausage. While still warm, add cream cheese and Cheddar cheese. Flatten biscuits; line each section of muffin tin with one biscuit. Spoon sausage mixture into biscuits; press closed. Bake according to biscuit instructions.

title: piquey cheese
directions: Blend together until well mixed.
Great for crackers.
Also makes delicious sandwiches.

title: island creamery sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix melted margarine with sweet potatoes and sugar.
Add to Bisquick, mixing thoroughly.
Knead lightly and pat out on floured board.
(May need to add extra Bisquick if too sticky.)
Grease baking pan and bake at 400° until done (approximately 15 to 20 minutes).
Makes 2 dozen.

title: applesauce chocolate chip cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream shortening with the 1 1/2 cups sugar until fluffy.
Add cocoa and beaten eggs.
Blend well.
Add applesauce.
Sift in dry ingredients until well blended.
Pour batter into greased and lightly floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with the 2 tablespoons sugar and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until cake tests done.
No frosting is needed.
Delicious with vanilla ice cream.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in microwave-safe dish in order listed.
Heat until cheese is melted and dip is bubbly.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and walnuts.
Put on bottom of 7 x 11-inch pan.
Next, in separate bowl, beat together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust. Lastly, mix lemon instant pudding with milk.
Pour on top of second layer.
Chill and top with Cool Whip and chopped walnuts. Serve.

title: chicken  and dumplings
directions: Put chicken chunks in pan with a small amount of water.
Bring to a boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Take "Butter Me Not" biscuits or Hungry Jack butter biscuits and pinch off into small pieces of dough and drop into chicken (boiling).
Stir until thick and doughy. Add butter and milk.
Bring to a second boil. Turn down to simmer and cook until dough is done.
Let cool and they should thicken up as they cool down a bit.

title: monster cookies
directions: Note:
There is no flour in this recipe.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, eggs (one at a time), flour, baking soda, vanilla, sour cream, nuts and then chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured tube pan.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour a 10 inch Bundt or tube pan, set aside. In a large bowl mix all dry ingredients together. Stir in butter and mix well. Add eggs, bananas and vanilla, mixing until well blended. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done. Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine 2 cans soup and water.
Place rice in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Lay chicken on top of rice.
Pour soup mixture on top of this. Sprinkle with pepper and paprika.
Put in a 250° oven. After it starts cooking, cover with foil.
(Probably wait 5 minutes.)
Cook for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: spicy apricot bread *
directions: Chop apricots in small pieces.
Mix apricots with next seven ingredients, bring to boil and boil five minutes.
Gradually stir in flour sifted together with soda until just blended.
Bake in well-greased bread pan at 330° for one hour or more.
Cool five minutes.
Remove and cool further on cake rack.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and baking soda; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat the eggs until light and fluffy.
Add the oil, sugars, zucchini and vanilla. Sift in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put margarine and peaches in oven until melted.
Mix sugar, Bisquick and milk together.
Pour over peaches and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Do not stir.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Melt the butter in a heavy saucepan (10 or 12-inch).
Mix all ingredients together, beating eggs and adding last.
Pour mixture into the hot pan of butter; stir until heated.
Put skillet in moderate oven (325°) to bake.
When crusted around edge and top, turn under and let crust again.
Do this twice, allowing the last crust to remain on sides and top.
Time required to bake is 40 to 60 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat well.
Pour into 8 1/2 x 12 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and beat well.
Combine the remaining ingredients and add to the first mixture.
Mix well. Fold in 1 cup raisins and 1 cup nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, cut up Velveeta and cream cheese and melt in microwave. After melted, put in crock-pot. Brown hamburger. Mix melted cheese, cream cheese and hamburger in crock-pot. Keep crock-pot on high until blended, then place on low.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring stock to a boil.
Add vegetables.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes or more if you like tender vegetables.

title: squash relish
directions: Cover squash, peppers and onions in salt water and let set 1 1/2 hours.
Do not rinse.
Bring to boil vinegar, sugar, mustard and celery seed.
Add squash, onion and pepper mixture and bring to a second boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Put mixture into jars and seal.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix 2 cups flour and confectioners sugar.
Cut in butter, work with hands into a dough.
Press in bottom and
1 1/2-inches up sides of a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet magic dill pickles
directions: Heat sugar, water and vinegar until dissolved.
Add pickles in solution and let cool.
Return to gallon pickle jar.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients to the creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Grease 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: refrito dip plate
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; spread on large dinner plate. Spread sour cream over refrito mixture.
Spread salsa over sour cream.
Top with diced vegetables.
Serve with Fritos or corn chips for dipping.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat well all together as you would any
cake.
Bake
1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Arrange banana slices on bottom of crust; set aside.
Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute or until well blended.
Pour mixture at once into crust. Cover with chocolate Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, gradually add cold water.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat, add butter and lemon juice.

title: apple cake
directions: Do not use electric mixer! Stir with a spoon.
Mix sugar, eggs, apples and oil and set aside.
Mix other ingredients, flour, vanilla and baking soda; add to sugar mixture and add pecans last. Pour into tube pan.
Bake one hour in 325° oven.

title: make your own brown sugar
directions: Blend sugar and molasses. Let it stand overnight in a covered container.

title: baked goober beanies
directions: Empty one can of pork and beans in a casserole dish.
Combine the brown sugar and mustard and sprinkle half over the beans.
Top with the other can of beans and sprinkle with the remaining sugar, chopped bacon and catsup.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: apple cranberry sauce
directions: Peel and cut apples; add remaining ingredients to pan.
Cook over medium heat.
Bring to a boil; mash and serve warm or cold.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Take Tabouli mix and soak in 1 c. cold water, add all veg.
in mix and stir well then chill 12 hrs.

title: meat loaf italiano
directions: In a bowl, mix well 1/2 cup soup, beef, sausage, crumbs, cheese, onion, egg and Worcestershire sauce.
In baking pan, firmly shape into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
In saucepan, heat remaining soup, water and reserved drippings to boiling, stirring occasionally. Spoon over meat loaf.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix 2 cups milk, corn syrup and cocoa.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let mixture cool some.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add cooled mixture and rest of milk, then chill. When ready to churn, add whipping cream and vanilla.
Pour into freezer and churn ice cream.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in a small amount of lukewarm water (1/4 cup); set aside.
Dissolve salt, sugar and shortening in the hot water in large mixing bowl.
When mixture is lukewarm, add the yeast mixture and beaten eggs.
Add flour.
Mix all ingredients until dough forms elastic strands.
Turn out on floured board.
Roll and shape rolls.
Put on greased baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise about 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sun tea
directions: Empty contents of tea bags into a 1-quart preserving jar.
Add water and stir briskly.
Screw jar lid down tight so jar will not leak when turned upside down.
Set jar in a sunny window or outside in sunshine and leave until tea is as dark as strong coffee. Depending on the intensity of the sun, this takes from 4 to 8 hours.
At times during the day, turn the jar to mix as you pass by.
Strain tea through a small fine sieve after darkened into a clean 1-quart jar.
Place lid on tight and store in refrigerator.

title: basic cookie dough
directions: Measure flour, baking powder and salt into sifter.
Cream butter with sugar in large bowl until fluffy; beat in eggs.
Sift in dry ingredients, a quarter at a time, blending well to make a stiff dough.
Chill 1 hour, or until firm.
Divide dough into quarters; roll one at a time, to 1/8-inch thickness.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: banana cake (chiffon)
directions: Sift together salt, baking powder and flour. Add sugar to sifted mixture. Set aside mixture.
Separate the yolks from the whites of eggs.

title: tender baked ham
directions: Will also need a 1 turkey size oven bag.
Preparation time: 10 minutes.
Cooking Time:
2 to 2 1/2 hours

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread pieces in milk.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef; mix well.
Crumble ground beef into egg mixture; mix well.
Place mixture in a loaf pan, pressing down into a loaf shape.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Combine with bread and seasonings. Toss with enough liquid to moisten.
Makes 3 cups stuffing or enough stuffing for 4 to 5 pound chicken.
Double recipe for 10 lb. turkey.

title: cheesy tater casserole
directions: Cut potatoes in cubes and salt to taste.
Put in a casserole dish.
Dot potatoes with butter.
Melt Cheez Whiz in microwave. Pour over potatoes.
Cover with sour cream.
Add bacon; then green onion tops.
If necessary, warm in microwave for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.

title: bologna cake
directions: Spread cream cheese on bologna and layer slices like a cake. Coat the side of the cake with cream cheese.
Pat parsley on the side of the cake; put crumbled chips on the top of the cake. Place in freezer for one hour.
Slice in 6 equal slices and serve in wedges.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in frying pan.
While doing this, boil salted water and cook package of egg noodles.
(These noodles seem to cook really fast; be careful they don't get mushy.) Drain.
Add flour to hamburg.
Add small can mushrooms to ground beef and brown 1 minute.
Pour in the cans of soup and dilute with about 1/2 can of water.
Cover and simmer this about 5 minutes. Add 1/2 cup sour cream to this.
Stir in and simmer a few more minutes.
Pour over cooked noodles and serve warm.
Great reheated, too.

title: reuben meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/3 cup soup, ground beef, corned beef, bread crumbs, eggs, parsley and garlic.
On wax paper, pat meat firmly into a 12 x 15-inch rectangle.
In a small bowl, combine sauerkraut, caraway and shredded cheese.
Press into meat within 1-inch of edges. With aid of wax paper, roll meat tightly, jelly roll fashion, starting at short edge.
Seal seams and ends.
Place loaf, seam side down, in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Mix remaining soup and horseradish and spoon over loaf.
Bake 1 hour. Arrange cheese slices over top of loaf.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: sunflower seed slaw
directions: Remove seasoning packet from noodles; set aside.
Break noodles into pieces; place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until golden, stirring once; set aside.

title: mouth watering chili
directions: Soak beans overnight; rinse.
In a large pot, add enough water to cover beans by at least 2-inches. Bring to a boil and reduce heat to medium.
Add browned ground beef, drained, and next 10 ingredients.

Cover and simmer slowly for 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Add more hot water as needed, 1 cup at a time. Slowly add 1 cup of cool water to cornstarch. Add to simmering beans, 1/2 cup at a time, until thickened to preference.
