Freeze leftover chili for a quick meal another night.

title: orange loaf
directions: Place orange juice, rind, boiling water and raisins in a bowl.
Add sugar, soda, butter, vanilla, and egg.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Ice with thin powdered sugar icing if desired.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello, stir to dissolve; add pineapple and blueberries and pour into a 2 quart rectangular casserole dish and chill until set.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream and sugar, mix well and spread over chilled set jello mix.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Garnish with a few blueberries and pieces of pineapple, optional.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain and cool.
Pick out what remaining ingredients you like or have on hand and stir into macaroni with dressing.
Refrigerate.
Don't add cheese until ready to serve.

title: stuffed shells or manicotti
directions: Boil noodles in water plus 1 tablespoon oil al dente (slightly under-cooked).
Mix cheeses, parsley, salt, pepper and eggs. Drain shells.
Run cold water over shells.
Stuff each shell with cheese mixture and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole or two small casseroles.
Spoon sauce around.
Dish is now ready for baking or freezing.
If freezing, cover with heavy-duty foil, then thaw in refrigerator the night before cooking.

title: pumpkin bread(mom's recipe)
directions: Place all ingredients, except nuts, in a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Line pans with foil.
Makes 3 or 4 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple and juice, cornstarch and sugar until smooth. Add Cheddar cheese (shredded) and put into greased casserole dish. Crush Ritz crackers and add melted margarine. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: "pizza" pronto
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in Bisquick. Beat vigorously.
Turn onto surface, well dusted with Bisquick. Knead about 20 times.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Cut up vegetables and cook all in frying pan with heated bacon fat for just 7 minutes.
Serve with soy sauce.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Slice onions, saute in butter.
In
a greased casserole dish, put layer of onions, cheese and crumbled crackers.
(Two layers.) Put crackers on
top.
Dot
with butter; drizzle milk on top. Cook at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: perfect pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, salt, butter and syrup; beat well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Don't peek!! until it's done.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: tofu loaf
directions: Slice tofu into quarters.
Cook in salted water for 20 minutes.
Drain and crumble.
Mix the remaining ingredients, except for the soup.
Place the mixture into a greased loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Pour heated, undiluted cream of mushroom soup over the loaf.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cover cabbage with 1 quart boiling water, plus 1 teaspoon salt; boil 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Melt oleo and add flour; mix well.
Add 1 cup milk, white sauce should not be too thick.
Place cabbage in baking dish; add cheese and stir until melted.
Pour white sauce over cabbage, stir lightly. Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Place chicken breasts in a greased baking dish and top each piece with a slice of cheese.
Mix milk and soup together well and spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle dressing mix over all and drizzle butter on top.
Cover and cook at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cooked tomatoes
directions: Peel and cook tomatoes until done.
Add 1/8 teaspoon margarine and biscuits.
Add brown sugar, white sugar, 1/4 c. margarine and salt.
Put all ingredients in oven and bake until thick and consistency of pie.

title: candy apples
directions: Combine all ingredients except sticks for cooking in a saucepan.
Cook until mixture reaches 300° or hard brittle stage. Place sticks into apples.
Dip each apple into mixture.
Line a cookie sheet with wax paper and place apples on it.
Cool.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Place margarine and oatmeal in mixing bowl.
Pour 1 1/2 cup hot water over mix.
Let set for 20 minutes.
Sift together sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda.
Then add 2 eggs and mix. Add to the first mixture all at one time; mix well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix ingredients together in a saucepan.
Stir constantly over low to medium heat until it boils and thickens.
Pour over hot biscuits and enjoy!

title: creamy turkey kluski bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. In medium skillet, brown turkey with pepper and onion.
Stir in salt, margarine and basil.
Cook 1 minute.
Blend in soup and milk.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Combine noodles and turkey mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs, approximately 1/3 cup.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: japanese fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chips; mix sugar and eggs well.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 2 pie shells at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and pick off meat. Cream together soups, onion, salt and chicken. Spray dish and pour mixture into dish. Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package and spread over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: skillet chicken divan
directions: Heat oil in skillet on medium high heat.
Add chicken, cook and stir until browned.
Stir in soup, broccoli, water and sherry. Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese cornbread
directions: Put one half of mixture in greased pan.
Add half of cheese. Add remaining mixture and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: easy shrimp or fillet au gratin
directions: Arrange fish in a buttered dish or pan.
Dot with margarine and a little pepper.
Spread soup directly from can over fillets and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle top with paprika for good looks.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: speedy creamed seafood veggies
directions: Bring half and half to boiling in large pan.
Add pasta; return to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and zucchini.
Cover.
Simmer for 2 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Gently stir in seafood; cook until heated.

title: tuna chip casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 can water and 1/2 can milk in a large saucepan.
Flake in drained tuna.
Mix thoroughly while heating.
Crunch bag of potato chips into bits and mix into soup with tuna.
Stir until all chips are soaked.
Remove from heat and let sit a few minutes.
Stir and serve.
Garnish with shredded cheese.
Green peas are a good complement to the casserole.
Serves 2 or 3, but recipe can be doubled or tripled.

title: milnot cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla; add gelatin and blend well.
Fold in stiffly whipped Milnot.
(This can be done in electric mixer.)
Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter together; press 2/3 of mixture on bottom and sides of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (or larger).
Add filling and sprinkle remainder of crumbs on top.
Chill overnight.

title: carrot salad
directions: Bring tomato soup (undiluted) to boil.
Keep separate the pepper, onion and carrots; layer in casserole dish.
Add sugar, oil and vinegar to hot soup and mix.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Very good!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
(I usually put it in a strainer and run hot water over it to remove all fat.) Pour into casserole dish and stir in soup.
Arrange Tater Tots on top to completely cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until Tater Tots have browned.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: In large bowl, combine the broccoli and cauliflower.
Pour the dressing of mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar over the vegetables.

title: cottage cheese appetizers
directions: Cut favorite bread into a variety of shapes with a knife or cookie cutters.
Spread with cottage cheese.
Use your favorite garnish.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and chill.
Can be made the day before.

title: french potato salad(topped with edwards' hickory smoked bacon!)
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Reserve for garnish.
Boil potatoes until fork-tender; peel and slice into thin circles.
(Do not dice.)
Combine all remaining ingredients except garnish; mix well and pour over warm potatoes.
Mix very gently to prevent potatoes from breaking into pieces.
Place in serving bowl; cover and keep at room temperature until ready to serve.
When ready to serve, garnish with bacon, green onion and parsley.
Serves 6.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift first five ingredients into mixing bowl. Cut in shortening or 2 sticks margarine. Crumble yeast cake into warm water; stir until dissolved. Stir yeast mixture into buttermilk. Mix liquid with dry ingredients to form soft dough. This may be rolled out and baked or stored in refrigerator until needed. Biscuits may be rolled out, dipped in margarine and frozen. If frozen, let stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours or until thawed. Bake 25 minutes at 425°.

title: amish baked oatmeal
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients; mix well. Spread evenly in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Immediately spoon into bowls; add milk. Top with fruit and/or brown sugar, if desired. Yield: 6 servings.

title: rotel tomatoes
directions: Put all in hot jars and water bath for 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken and place bite size pieces into bottom of shallow casserole dish.
Spoon chicken soup over chicken to form an even layer.
Pour evaporated milk over top and cover with dressing mix. Top off with chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain and mash pears.
Bring 1 cup pear juice to a boil and add jello, stirring until dissolved.
Whip in cream cheese and let chill until it starts to get thick.
Add whipped Dream Whip and fold in pears.
Pour into mold.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Add sweet potatoes and milk; stir until moistened.
Roll out dough on a lightly floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out biscuits with a 2-inch cutter and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Yields 18 biscuits.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add egg, then applesauce.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time.
Then add raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into large loaf pan, Teflon or line pan with wax paper.
(Makes two small loaf pans.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done, testing with a toothpick in the middle of cake until toothpick is clean.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Brown ground beef and drain. Line bottom of casserole dish with crushed Doritos.
Combine ground beef, Ranch Style beans, Rotel and Spanish rice.
Mix together well.
Pour over crushed Doritos.
Cover with shredded cheese.

title: soft "archway" cookies
directions: Sift together first four ingredients; set aside.
Beat together oil and sugar; add egg.
Alternately blend in flour mixture with milk, adding in vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Ice cookies with favorite icing.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: crabbies i
directions: Heat garlic in butter until softened but not browned.
Cool. Mix garlic butter, cheese, mayonnaise, crabmeat and Tabasco. Spread on crumpets.
Cut each in quarters.
If desired, freeze on cookie sheets, then store in plastic bags.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in skillet. Drain and add tomato sauce, catsup and pepper.
In small casserole dish, alternate meat mixture and cheese slices; arrange biscuits around edge.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Melt margarine
in
a
3-quart
saucepan over low heat. Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly until marshmallows are melted
and
mixture
is
syrupy.
Remove
from heat immediately; add Rice Krispies and stir to coat evenly.
Press warm mixture evenly
into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool. Cut into bars. Makes 32.

title: kraut salad
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to boil until sugar is dissolved. Cool and pour over remaining ingredients.
Will keep a long time in refrigerator.

title: crock-pot seafood chowder
directions: Thaw fish fillets and cut into bite-size pieces.
In small skillet, saute pork and onion until golden; drain and put into crock-pot with fish.
Add all remaining ingredients except evaporated milk.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 9 hours until potatoes are tender (high 2 to 3 hours).
Add evaporated milk last half hour.
Serve in large bowl with French bread.

title: deluxe breakfast casserole
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer half of the bread, then half of the ham or sausage, and then American cheese. Over the American cheese, layer the rest of the bread, the rest of the ham or sausage and then the Swiss cheese.

title: squash pie
directions: Cook squash until done.
Drain and mash.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° until they turn brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: fresh guacamole
directions: Peel avocados; remove seed and mash to preferred consistency. Peel and chop tomato and add to mashed avocado.
Finely dice onion and add to mixture.
Add spices to mixture.
Add juice of lime. Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: new orleans shrimp creole
directions: In skillet with butter brown onions, garlic, green pepper and celery.
Cook uncovered about 20 minutes (until tender).
Add tomatoes, brown sugar, salt, pepper and bay leaves.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and shrimp.
Cover and simmer 6 to 8 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6. Easy and good.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Combine flour, sugar and yeast in large bowl.
Gradually add warm water to dry ingredients and beat well.
Cover with transparent wrap.
Let stand in warm place 2 days.
Use as directed in Sourdough Bread.
Always feed starter before using in bread.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Drain clams.
Add to clam juice the garlic, butter, onions, basil, oregano and parsley and cook until tender.
Blend in soup and wine and cook until bubbly.
Add drained clams; warm through and serve over cooked linguine.

title: crabcakes
directions: Clean crabmeat and drain. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top of crab.
In a separate bowl, beat rest of ingredients (except for butter) into a sauce.
Fold this mixture into crabmeat and bread crumbs.
Grease cookie sheet with butter. Scoop mixture into ice cream scooper to form shape of crabcake.
Place on cookie sheet and put a thin slice of butter on top of each crabcake.
Broil until golden brown. Recipe makes 6 crabcakes.

title: mother jean's turkey dressing
directions: Mix flour, meal, eggs and melted margarine in a large bowl. Add milk but keep it stiff enough.
Bake at 350° until brown. Cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a moderate oven at 350° about 1 hour.
Set in water to bake.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix with 1 1/2 sticks of butter, melted.
Mix well.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: berry mousse
directions: Mix gelatin according to package.
Add Cool Whip and blend. Stir in strawberries gently.
Pour or spoon into dessert glasses or cups.
Top with a strawberry.
Chill about 2 hours.

title: walla walla onion pie
directions: Prepare and partially bake a crust to fit a 9-inch pan, using a basic pie dough recipe.
Saute onions in oil and butter over low heat until golden yellow.
Beat together the eggs, half and half, flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg, then add onions and half of the grated cheese.
Pour into crust; sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: steak brasciole
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
In medium bowl place first 8 ingredients and mix well.
Put filling in pounded meat at the widest end of steak.
Roll meat so that seam is underneath.
Place on greased baking dish and spread a little olive oil over the meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until mixture is cooked through.
Serve with your favorite brown gravy.
Delicious!

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter over medium heat; add onion and cook for 40 to 50 minutes, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle flour over onion; cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add broth, wine, pepper and thyme. Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes. Ladle soup into 8 individual baking dishes.
Top with toasted bread slices.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Broil for 2 to 3 minutes to melt cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grandma's chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add peanut butter; stir until melted.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls.
Set aside.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax together.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate mixture.
Use toothpick to remove covered balls from mixture.
Set on waxed paper until chocolate sets.

title: masters salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a small container.
Add m.s.g., if wanted.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Tear or cut lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and mix.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all together. Put in oven at 350° until knife comes out clean, about 1 hour.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Add 1 tablespoon salt to rapidly boiling water. Gradually add egg noodles so that water continues to boil. Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender. Drain in colander. Melt butter or margarine in top of double boiler over boiling water. Blend in flour; add turkey broth and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Add turmeric, wine, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. Remove from heat and stir in heavy cream. Add 1/2 the sauce to the noodles and place in greased shallow baking dish. Add turkey, mushrooms and almonds to the remaining sauce. Place turkey mixture in the center of the noodles and sprinkle top with a mixture of Parmesan and Swiss cheese. Bake in a moderate 375° oven for 30 minutes or until topping is lightly browned. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cabbage to freeze
directions: Mix the cabbage, carrots, peppers and salt.
Let stand 1 hour. Then mix the remaining ingredients.
Boil for 1 minute and let cool.
Pour over slaw.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and grate potatoes.
Add eggs; stir.
Sift meal; add to mixture.
Add milk in potatoes.
Add butter.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Stir.
Bake at 350° another 1/2 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put 1/2 stuffing mix in bottom of a baking dish.
Place a layer of chicken over stuffing.
Pour soups over chicken; then put the rest of the stuffing over chicken and soup.
Pour 1 1/2 cans of broth over mixture.
Cover lightly with aluminum foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in pie shell.
Cook at 325° for about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with either chopped pecans or chopped walnuts.

title: sunshine salad(need a little sunshine?  try this salad.)
directions: Mix gelatin in cold water.
Add sugar, salt and hot pineapple juice and stir until dissolved.
Add orange juice and vinegar, then let cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, add other ingredients.
Mold and chill.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Add next six ingredients and cook until thickened a little.
Cook noodles and drain, adding oil to the water to avoid sticking.
Grease 2 1/2-quart casserole. Arrange in layers:
meat mixture, Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese.
Repeat once and end with meat and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Stir in coconut and Rice Krispies.
Press into a buttered 9-inch pie pan, going up sides. Freeze.
Fill with ice cream right before serving.
(I like to use mint chip ice cream the best.)
Use more than 1 quart if serving 8.

title: yellow bean dressing
directions: Dissolve dry ingredients.
Boil (medium heat) until thick, stirring all the time.
Pour over cooked beans and add parsley.

title: fajita tacos
directions: Cut up fajita meat in small strips. Marinate in fajita marinade mixture.
Brown meat in skillet, adding onion, pepper, garlic and comino.
Cook to desired consistency.
Serve on tortillas with garnishes of choice (salsa, lettuce, tomatoes, etc.).

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Spread in baked shell.
Let sit in refrigerator while whipping the cream.
Whip cream until it forms peaks.
Fold in drained pineapple and nuts.
Spread on top of butter mixture.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Melt together soup and cheese (on low heat).
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen colorful punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 4 cups boiling water; add 9 additional cups of water.
Add sugar, lemon juice, pineapple juice and almond extract.
Freeze in non-breakable container.
Take out of freezer 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. This can be frozen in ice trays or different shaped molds to have ice cubes with your punch (for those of us who have to have our ice).

title: rich coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add coconut extract; mix well.
Fold in egg whites and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Set oven temperature to 325°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Drizzle glaze over top and side of cake.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Coarsely chop artichoke hearts and place in a medium ovenproof serving dish.
Add the mayonnaise, scallions, spinach, grated cheese and spices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and serve with sturdy crackers or bread rounds.
Tortilla chips also go great with this dish.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Heat milk.
Blend sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk and cook on low heat until thick.
Beat egg yolks and add custard to yolks. Cook 3 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: microwave corned beef and cabbage
directions: Clean and chop cabbage.
Place it in a microwave cooking dish. Salt and pepper it.
Sprinkle the cabbage liberally with water. Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir cabbage and add more water if it appears dry.
Cook for another 3 minutes and stir again. Continue doing this until the cabbage is nearly done, always checking to see if it needs more water.
When the cabbage is nearly done, add the corned beef.
Mix well.
Finish cooking the cabbage.
Serve hot.

title: peasant's fare
directions: Mix cabbage, Ragu/Prego and seasonings in large soup pot.
Add sauteed and drained meat seasonings.
Simmer as long as possible (at least 1 hour).
Serve with corn bread or Italian bread.
Great the next day!!

title: mimi's easy fruit cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Break into small pieces. Add fruit and nuts.
Make frosting mix according to directions on package.
Add to cake and fruit mixture.
Mix well with hands. Pack tightly into pans.
Use tube or loaf pans.
Line pans with foil before packing.
Chill in fridge for 24 hours before cutting. Makes 6 1/2 pound cake.

title: low-fat cheese cake
directions: In blender, mix eggs, yogurt and vanilla.
Add flour, honey and bananas.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until set. Cool.
Top with cherries, strawberries, etc.

title: pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in a heavy saucepan. Cook until syrup reaches the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add vanilla and beat until it begins to thicken. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Yields about 18 pralines

title: yum yum salad
directions: Place jello, hot water and cheese in pan and stir over low heat until cheese is blended well into mixture.
Remove from heat, add pineapple and nuts. Place in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Add dream whip and refrigerate. This makes a nice mold.

title: ham and green beans with potatoes
directions: Place ham in heavy kettle.
Add 2 inches of water and cook slowly, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes and green beans (a little water if needed) and continue cooking slowly for another hour, or until meat is tender and the potatoes are soft.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix and beat with mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Bake in greased stem pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix everything together. Top with bread crumbs.
Cover with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in buttered casserole dish. Great with ham.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Cook apples and stir in sugar, butter and spices; let cool. Combine flour, salt and shortening to make dough.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in 5-inch round (use saucer for pattern).
Put filling on half of dough, staying 1/2-inch from edge of pastry. Brush edge with water and fold pastry in half.
Seal edge with fork.
Prick pies 2 to 3 times with fork.
Fry in fat at 360° until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs for 20 minutes.
Cool in cold water and take off shells.
Cut in half and remove yolk.
Place yolks in bowl.
Add a squirt of mustard, a teaspoon of salt and a couple of shakes of paprika after you smush yolks to small pieces.
Mix well.
Place halved whites on a plate and fill with mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: great-grandma's coffee cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Set aside 3/4 cup of mixture for top.
Combine remaining mixture with eggs, buttermilk vanilla and baking soda and beat.
Add topping.
Bake approximately 35 minutes or until firm in center in 350° oven.
Use either 2 round pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Put sugar, vinegar and oil in pan and bring almost to the boiling point.
Let cool a few minutes.
Mix thoroughly with chopped vegetables.
Keep marinating it until it is well flavored. Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: raspberry chicken(makes 4 servings)
directions: Cut chicken breast halves in half lengthwise to make 8 pieces. Lightly salt chicken.
Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet.
Add chicken; cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Add onion around edges of skillet.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Transfer chicken to a platter; keep warm.
Add jelly, vinegar and brown sugar to mixture remaining in skillet.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a large saucepan.
Add evaporated milk, salt, corn syrup and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil, without stirring, for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla.
Cool. Keeps well in refrigerator for several weeks.
May be microwaved to heat.
Serve over ice cream.

title: sour cream cheese cake
directions: Mix and spoon in spring-form pan.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: cranberry squares
directions: For Base: Combine margarine, 1 cup flour and confectioners sugar.
Mix to crumbly mixture. Spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Don't cook.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt in large bowl.
Beat milk, peanut butter, spread, egg and vanilla; stir into flour mixture, just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pan, filling each cup 3/4 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes, remove from pan. Makes 12

title: pull taffy
directions: Boil syrup, sugar and vinegar to a hard ball stage (265°). Remove from the heat.
Add butter, baking soda and salt.
Stir only enough to blend.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Butter hands when able to handle.
Start pulling and folding until taffy turns white and becomes hard to pull.
Pull taffy into one long twisted strand, about 1-inch diameter.
Cut with scissors into bite size pieces.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients until thoroughly mixed.
Store in airtight container.

title: spinach rounds
directions: Remove crusts from bread; cut in rounds (4 per slice).
Blend spinach, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Stir in cucumbers, lemon juice and dill.
Chill for 2 hours, covered.
Spread spinach mixture on bread round and top with a light shake of paprika. Serve with tea or as a cocktail hors d'oeuvre.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter banana milkshake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Whir for 1 minute.
Add ice cubes and whir for 1 minute more on high.

title: vermicelli salad(servings:  15)
directions: Make French dressing in traditional style except substitute regular oil for sesame oil and add soy sauce instead of salt.

title: spunky spareribs
directions: Place ribs meaty side down in shallow roasting pan.
Roast in 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Turn ribs and roast 30 more minutes.
Again, drain off fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; brush on ribs.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Roast ribs, covered, for 1 hour, brushing with sauce occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate coconut crunchers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

In large bowl, combine cake mix, butter and eggs; mix well. Add coconut, walnuts, corn flakes, rolled oats and chocolate chips; mix well. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set. Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in blender.
Drop in 1 or 2 ice cubes into mixture.
Chop in blender with speed on mix.
Continue until all ice cubes are crushed.
Serve in tall glass.

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda and sugar in sifter.
Stir butter to soften.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add water and mix until all flour is dampened.
Add chocolate and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: golden mushroom chicken
directions: Use large skillet and brown chicken in oil, then remove.
Put mushroom soup and seasonings in skillet and stir well.
Then return chicken to skillet and cover.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Stir now and then.
Stir in milk and cook another 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: sausage and noodle casserole
directions: Cook sausage and onion in skillet "like making chili." Cook noodles and drain.
Mix celery soup and milk.
Let get hot; don't boil.
Add cheese and mix well.
Mix sausage and soup with noodles.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Crumble potato chips on top. Bake in a 350° oven
for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: spinach bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornbread mix.
Stir in last. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: festive rice pilaf
directions: In large, heavy saucepan or pot, heat oil.
Add onion, celery and carrot; cook until onion is soft, about 7 minutes.
Add rice, sunflower seeds, red pepper, garlic and thyme.
Saute another 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add stock and bay leaf; cover tightly and simmer about 50 minutes, until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
If desired, sunflower seeds may be added at the end of cooking time to preserve crunchiness.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: chicken broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone.
Cut into bite-size pieces. Cook broccoli by package directions.
Layer chicken and broccoli in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine broth, mayonnaise, juice, salt, pepper and soup.
Pour over chicken and broccoli. Cover with cheese; top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 30 minutes or unti hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: super hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in soup pot.
Drain off all fat. Add potatoes, carrots, celery, cabbage and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and other ingredients except peas.
Cover and simmer 50 minutes.
Add peas and cook another 5 to 10 minutes. Put in bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings, 200 calories each.

title: molasses ginger cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
I cream sugar and oleo, then add egg and cream some more.
Mix all other dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour, then roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Space 2 to 3 inches apart on cookie sheet.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Add onion and saute over moderate heat for 2 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup of the water.
Cover the skillet; reduce heat to low and steam the onion for 1 hour.
Add chicken, pepper, tomato and paprika.
Season with salt and pepper and stir in remaining 1/4 cup water.
Cover and cook for 35 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve with sour cream separately.
Serve with egg, barley or boiled rice.

title: chicken "pick-ups"(serves 25)
directions: Wash and clean wings.
Cut off tips and discard.
Cut in two at joints.
Drain and dry thoroughly on paper towel, placing in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with Accent, salad dressing and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover and let marinate several hours or overnight.

title: pizza crust
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pizza pan.
In medium size bowl, stir together 1 cup flour, yeast and salt.
Add very warm water and shortening.
Mix until almost smooth by hand.
Gradually stir in the remaining 1 1/2 cups flour to make firm dough.
Cover.
Let sit for 15 minutes.
Roll out dough and press into pan.
Generously prick dough with a fork.
Prebake for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges turn light brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into buttered casserole (sweeten, according to apples).
Mix together butter, sugars and flour and sprinkle over apples.
Add water.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Then lower to 375° and bake until apples are tender.

title: grandma's custard pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour 1/4 cup scalded milk in egg mixture.
Stir well.
Then slowly add rest of milk, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes; turn down to 375° until firm.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix cornmeal and onion.
Add egg and milk.
Drop by teaspoon into very hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cream of peanut soup(very different and delicious - williamsburg recipe)
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, then peanut butter, stirring until melted. Gradually stir in broth.
Return to heat.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cream and heat through.
Serves 10.
Preparation time is 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together chicken, soup, Veg-All and broth. Put into large casserole dish. Combine flour, milk, baking powder and margarine in bowl. Pour over top mixture. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Freezes well.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer half of ham, potatoes and onion in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining half.
Spoon undiluted soup over top.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or high 4 hours.

title: barbecue sauce for oven sliced ham
directions: Combine all ingredients, simmer for 1 hour.
Add ham and cook for 5 minutes.
Slice ham very thin.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Cool Whip containers are good to put this in.
Take out amount you want and put in same amount of 7-Up and serve cool!
Serve kind of icy (punch will be yellow).

title: bean dip
directions: Layer in a pan.
Heat through.
Can be used as dip with chips or put in tortillas.

title: cheese straws
directions: Soften butter.
Grate cheese.
Sift flour, red pepper and salt together.
Add cheese and butter, then add to flour mixture until ball is formed that will not stick to fingers.

title: perfect peach pickles
directions: Make a thick syrup of the sugar, water and vinegar.
Drop in the cloves and cinnamon.
Bring to boil and then carefully put in the prepared peaches.
(Cook just enough of the peaches to make one quart at a time.)

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade with milk; add Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie shell. Refrigerate until stiff (2 to 3 hours) before serving.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon together, then add Crisco, pumpkin, eggs and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: roasting beets
directions: Heat broiler. Cut sweet pepper into quarters; remove seeds. Brush with the 1 teaspoon olive oil. Place on broiler pan, skin sides up. Broil peppers about 4-inches from heat for 5 to 6 minutes or until skin darkens.
Remove to small bowl; cover with plastic wrap. Let stand 5 minutes. Peel off skins and discard; cut peppers into 1/4-inch dices.

title: hershey kiss cookies
directions: Beat and mix well and roll into 1-inch balls, then roll into some sugar. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. After baking and while still hot, get Hershey Kisses and press 1 into the center of each cookie.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage and tomato soup; set aside. Boil head of cabbage in salted water 5 to 7 minutes.
Separate leaves remove heavy vein from each leaf.
Fold leaf around 2 tablespoon meat filling.
Place in greased casserole.
Cover with undiluted tomato soup and bake in 350° oven 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 12 rolls.
Can be cooked in pressure cooker on 15 pounds for 10 minutes.

title: southern pie
directions: Combine Grape-Nuts and water; let stand until water is absorbed.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, corn syrup, salt, vanilla and melted butter.
Fold in the softened Grape-Nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until filling is puffed completely across the top.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain grease.
Add spaghetti sauce, onions and peppers and simmer.
Mix cottage cheese, egg and 3/4 of grated cheese.
In a cake pan, put enough sauce to cover bottom, then add a layer of noodles.
Top with a layer of cottage cheese mixture.
Repeat layers, ending up with sauce on top layer. Sprinkle with remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: yummy chocolate cake
directions: Beat well (4 minutes or so).
Add 12 ounce package chocolate chips.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
No frosting needed.

title: kookie cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs. Add vanilla and sour cream. Mix well. Add flour, soda and salt a little at a time. Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheets. Mix together the sugar and cinnamon. Grease the bottom of a juice glass, dip in the sugar mixture and slightly flatten the cookies. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add sugar and tomato soup.
Cook noodles.
Drain and add chicken soup.
Layer hamburg mixture first, then a layer of noodle mixture, then some cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top quite heavily with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, biscuit mix, egg, oil and milk.
Pour half in greased casserole.
Top with chilies and grated cheese.
Pour on rest of batter and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry molded salad
directions: *Cool Whip may be omitted.

title: linda's nutty cheese ball
directions: Combine all 3 cheeses in a bowl.
Chill until able to shape into a ball.
Roll ball in pecans and chill until ready to serve.

title: iced cappuccino frappe
directions: Combine all the above ingredients in a blender; blend until smooth.
Garnish with scoop of sherbet or ice cream if desired. Makes about 3 cups or 2 (12 ounce) servings.

title: fresh mushroom soup
directions: Saute onions in butter; add mushrooms to onions.
Cook on low, covered, for 5 minutes.
In large pot, make roux with flour and oil.
Add broth, water and cubes.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Cook until thickened.
Add pepper, but no salt.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies very fine in food processor or by hand. Layer 1/2 of the crumbs in container or large dish that resembles a flower pot. Blend cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar until light; add vanilla and fold in whipped topping. Combine pudding mix and milk; fold into cheese mixture. Pour in container over crumbs. Top with remaining crumbs to look like potting soil.

title: golden cheddar chicken bake
directions: Combine chicken, celery, cheese, mayonnaise, almonds, onions, lemon juice and salt.
Mix lightly.
Pour into baking dish.
Toss Corn Flakes crumbs and margarine together; sprinkle over mixture. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: salad of boston lettuce and blueberries
directions: In a small bowl or a jar, whisk or shake together blueberry or white-wine vinegar, walnut and vegetable oils, mustard, salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon water.
(The vinaigrette can be prepared up to 2 days ahead and stored, covered, in the refrigerator.)

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add flour alternately with eggs, and lemon extract.
Fold in 7-up. Pour into lightly greased tube pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Fold in pecans and parsley.
Add mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator; freezes well.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, butter and peanut butter.
Pour over cereal mix until coated.
In grocery bag, place powdered sugar and chocolate covered cereal.
Shake until all cereal is coated white (may add more powdered sugar).
Keep in airtight container.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and then add eggs.
Cream again.
Add jam and cream again.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Preheat oil in a frying pan.
Dip bread in egg mixture.
Brown on both sides. Serve with syrup.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in zucchini, flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Add the nuts.
Beat all together until well blended.
Add pineapple.
Stir in gently.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs and blend.
Stir in squash and alternate additions of milk and dry ingredients.
Stir in coconut.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.
Serves 16.
(Serve with lemon sauce, if desired.)

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and cocoa well and add remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Best with caramel icing.

title: cherry o cream cheese pie
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix well, then line dish with cracker mixture; push firm to all sides.

title: pluck it cake
directions: Melt butter, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Quarter biscuits. Grease tube cake pan.
Put layer of biscuits.
Pour mixture on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Layer of biscuits (repeat).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet crisp pickles(lime)
directions: Slice cucumbers, then cover the slices with a solution of lime in 2 gallons of water and soak 24 hours.
(Get slake lime from your local lumber yard.)

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until cake is moist.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: uncle ed's hush puppies
directions: Use a tablespoon to drop into deep fat at 375° until brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in order given; chill, then form in balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and press flat with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350°.
Don't overbake.
Remove from cookie sheet to a wire rack and cool.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pie shell; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix the salt and celery seed.
Mix the sugar and apple cider. Spread the salt and celery seed mixture over the cucumbers and onions. Let stand outside refrigerator for 1 hour. Stir occasionally.
Pour sugar and cider mixture over cucumber mix. Cover and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: egg pastry(1940)
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut lard into mixture until it looks like corn meal.
Mix egg, vinegar and water together and add gradually to flour mixture until dough holds together.

title: calico bean pot
directions: Cut bacon into bite-size pieces.
Saute in skillet or microwave until done.
Dip out of grease.
Discard all grease besides 1 1/2 tablespoons.
Saute onion.
Drain all the beans and discard liquid.
Add beans, bacon, sugar, vinegar, mustard and garlic salt to onions.
Microwave 30 minutes.

title: garlic-parmesan cheese bread
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients together.
Dip French bread slices in quietly, covering both sides.
Roll until completely covered in Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: missouri dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Make dumplings and roll in balls and roll in flour.
Drop in broth often, adding a little milk. Thicken with flour and water in a cup and pour in broth.

title: great casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in oil.
Combine meat mixture, macaroni, salt, pepper, corn, soup, olives and Tabasco. Turn into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple with juice and Jell-O until Jell-O dissolves, not to get very hot.
Set aside to cool.
Mix Cool Whip and buttermilk until smooth.
Add this to Jell-O mixture until well mixed.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate until set.
Sprinkle with nuts.
This is unusual, but good.

title: chocolate pizza 2
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces almond bark in a 2-quart bowl on High 2 minutes.
Stir.
Continue to microwave until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts. Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle with coconut. Microwave 2 ounces of almond bark and oil in 1 cup measuring cup for 1 minute. Stir.
Continue to microwave until smooth.
Drizzle over coconut.
Refrigerate until firm. Cut into wedges.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Continue to bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: quick party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in fruit punch bowl.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients at medium speed.
Sift cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda with flour, then add to mixture.
Next, add the jam.
Remove from mixer. Coat pecans and raisins with flour, then stir into mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After cooled, remove from pan and, if desired, soak with whiskey by wrapping a soaked cloth around the cake and storing.
May be frozen.

title: d'alessio's anise delights
directions: In large pot, mix sugar, sweet butter, eggs, flour, baking powder, anise, salt and oil until it becomes dough.
Take out of pot and knead the dough on the table.
(Put flour on table.)
Take small pieces and roll in your hands like a snake and shape into a hill.
Place cookies on nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes (no longer).
Makes about 25 cookies (hills).

title: brownie fruit delight
directions: Bake brownie according to package directions. Mix cream cheese and pineapple; slice banana and strawberries. Set aside. When brownie is cool, spread cream cheese mixture on top. Cover with sliced strawberries and banana. Drizzle with chocolate sauce; sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: blitz torte
directions: Alternate milk with flour.
Add the vanilla.
Bake in 2 layers (very thin).
Cover with the egg whites, beaten stiff with 3/4 cup sugar and nuts.
Put the whites on before baking the cake.

title: orange rum cake
directions: Halve oranges. Squeeze juice and clean out shells. Fill shells with orange sherbet. Wrap with plastic wrap and freeze. Can decorate with sprig of mint or cherries. Serve to cleanse palate for a formal dinner or at a brunch.

title: 8 can soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Combine all ingredients.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in large casserole dish.
Set aside.
Cut shortening in flour; add milk.
Roll dough thin; cover with apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up.
Slice roll in one-inch slices.
Place in melted margarine.
Heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Pour over apple slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend sugar and flour.
Stir into eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Turn into 2 greased pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: congealed salads
directions: Put jello in 2 cups boiling water to dissolve.
Add crushed pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until congealed.

title: sweet-n-hot meatballs
directions: Mix sauce and cranberry together.
Heat over low flame.
Brown meat as meatballs.
After browned, place in sauce and simmer.

title: barbecue beef sauce
directions: Mix together and simmer for 2 minutes.
Serve mixed with shredded, cooked beef.
I use a chuck roast, cooked until it's well done and then shred it.
The shredding is the most time consuming.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Bone and chop chicken.
Layer a 2-quart dish with Doritos. Put chicken on next.
Combine the rest of the ingredients (except cheese) and put on chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cut chicken into strips (2 inches or so).
Salt, pepper and flour breasts (first).
Bring to boil water, rice, 1 tablespoon oleo and salt.
Turn down to simmer and simmer 15 minutes, then do breasts.
Brown them in 1/2 cup oleo.
Remove from pan; saute onions.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add sour cream to soup mixture. Add cooked rice.
Season to taste.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken breast in rice mixture.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until vegetables are done.
Best made the day before.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Thaw hash brown potatoes.
Place rolls on ungreased pizza pan. Sprinkle with potatoes and sausage that has oil drained off.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour onto crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: play dough(yield: 1 quart)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large saucepan.
Add oil and water until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture leaves the sides of the pan.
Turn out on waxed paper and knead in food coloring.
Keep in an airtight container.

title: chicken and cashews
directions: Cut chicken fillets into slivers.
Combine bouillon, cornstarch and soy sauce in bowl; mix well.
Heat oil in wok.
Add garlic; cook until brown.
Discard garlic.
Add chicken; stir-fry for 1 to 2 minutes.
Push to side of wok.
Add green onions; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Push to side of wok.
Repeat with pea pods, mushrooms and bamboo shoots.
Add soy sauce mixture; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Mix all ingredients together; add cashews.
Serve over hot, cooked rice or chow mein noodles.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Divide cheese 9 ways.
Sprinkle one part cheese on one tortilla.
Roll and place in pan.
Continue with other 7 tortillas.
Pour enchilada sauce over rolls.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: annie's breakfast casserole
directions: Mix ham, bread and cheese in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish (broccoli optional).
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over first ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Watch closely.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Very good!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken into pot and cover with water.
Add salt and onion.
Boil gently until tender.
Remove from bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Place chicken in casserole dish and pour chicken broth over chicken.
Add desired amount of peas and carrots (optional).
Then spread can of celery soup over chicken.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart glass batter bowl, blend sugar and syrup.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until syrup turns a light brown color.
Stir in butter, peanuts and vanilla, mixing well. Microwave (High) 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Place bowl on a cloth hot pad as it will be very hot.
Gently stir in baking soda until light and foamy.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Working quickly, cool partially by lifting edges with spatula so mixture won't stick. When firm but still warm, turn over.
Pull mixture thin.
When cool, break into small pieces.
Makes 1 pound.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, mayo and vinegar and pour over broccoli; serve!

title: mince apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Toss apples with 2 tablespoons flour; arrange in pastry shell.
Top with mincemeat.
In small bowl, combine remaining flour, sugar and cinnamon; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Mix in nuts.
Sprinkle over mincemeat.
Bake 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.
Serve warm or cold with vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges, reserve 1 cup juice.
Add juice to pudding.
Cook until thick. Pour over fruit while hot.
Chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, add bananas.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda; set aside.
Cream butter, sugar, pudding mix and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until creamy and smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.) Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
Approximately 7 dozen.
tags: serving size vanilla instant pudding mix

title: j. d.'s barbecue sauce
directions: Mix pickling spice, sage and lemon in small saucepan.
Boil about 15 minutes.
Cover and let set awhile.
Set aside.

title: potato salad(kartoffelsalat)
directions: Place potatoes in bowl.
Mix together the sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over potatoes and mix well.
Add onion, pickle, green pepper and parsley.
Toss well, sprinkling with salt and pepper. Chill.
Serve cold.
Makes 4 servings.

title: confetti cheese spread
directions: With food processor or electric mixer, blend together Cheddar and cream cheese until well blended.
Add chopped green pepper and remaining ingredients.
Process until well blended.
Serve with crackers.
Spread is better if prepared the night before it is to be served.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine above ingredients and shape into loaf.

title: smoked turkey and rice casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crispy, reserving drippings.
Blend flour, salt and pepper into 1/2 cup bacon drippings.
Add milk, slowly, stirring until thick and smooth.
Add 2/3 of cubed cheese; stir until somewhat melted.
Fold in turkey, pimento, rice and crumbled bacon.
Pour into two buttered 1 1/2-quart casseroles or three 1-quart casseroles.
Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.
(Wrap and freeze one.)
This is great for after the holidays using your leftover turkey.

title: mother's bread butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions.
Add salt; cover with cracked ice or ice cubes.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours; drain well. Rinse and drain well again.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and shortening until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Add to the rest of the crumb mixture: water, molasses, soda and salt.
Put in a large greased pan.
Put the reserved one cup of crumbs on top of mixture and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coffee cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in a little water.
Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream together margarine and peanut butter.
Gradually add 3 boxes of sugar.
May have to use hand to mix.
Shape into balls. Melt in top of double boiler the chocolate chips and wax.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper to harden.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise, beef, onion, pepper and Accent.
Form into ball.
Roll in nuts.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine popped corn and nuts in a large roasting pan.
In medium saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, oleo and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 4 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda and vanilla. Pour over popcorn and nuts; toss to coat well. Bake for 60 minutes in a 250° oven, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool and break apart.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: rice dinner
directions: Heat margarine and liquid aminos in large frying pan.
Saute onions, green peppers and mushrooms in margarine/aminos mixture until onions are translucent.
Add cooked rice and mix together. Serve hot.

title: orange delight cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in sour milk.
Mix ingredients together.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake.
While hot dip in the following:

title: holly farms potatoes
directions: Wash off the potatoes and let them soak while you mix all the dry ingredients in a big Ziploc bag.
(The potatoes need to be damp when you coat them.)
Put each potato wedge in the Ziploc bag and shake well to coat.
Place the coated potatoes in a shallow casserole dish.
Pour melted margarine over the potatoes.
Cook 30 minutes at 400°.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Mix dressings and seasonings together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Can also use other vegetable of your choice.
This tastes very good.

title: crock-pot beef in mushroom gravy
directions: Cut steak or venison into serving size pieces and place in the crock-pot.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over meat. Cook on high for 5 to 8 hours.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: In a large pot, put 2 to 3 gallons of water to boil. When it starts to boil, pour oil off the jar of roux and put the roux in the pot. Stir the roux until dissolved; add the chicken and the seasonings. Cook until the chicken is done enough to take out and debone. Cut up sausage. Put the chicken and sausage in the roux and cook for about an hour.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Make jello according to directions, add strawberries, bananas, pineapple and cake.
Tear cake into small pieces.
Mix well and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and let jell.
Mix pudding according to directions and pour over jello.
Cool for 1 hour.
Add Cool Whip on top.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, bring broth to simmer.
Add barley and peppercorns.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt butter in medium pan and saute onion and celery 5 minutes. Add mushrooms and saute for 5 minutes longer.
When barley is almost done, add mushroom mixture and carrots and simmer until done.
Mix sherry and flour.
Stir into soup.
Cook 15 minutes and adjust seasoning.
Before serving, sprinkle with parsley.

title: tri level brownies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Stir in margarine and put into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Melt chocolate; add margarine, sugar and egg and beat well.
Add the next 6 ingredients to the chocolate mixture and spread over the baked layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool; frost with fudge frosting.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Drain pineapple until all
juice is off.
Then mix rice, sugar, marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip, mix well. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Moisten bread crumbs with milk.
Combine with ground beef, salt and pepper.
Shape mixture into patties.
Place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients to make barbecue sauce.
Pour around patties.
Set baking dish in oven and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until soft (3 to 4 minutes) and add rice, peas, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well; cover pan and heat over very low heat for a few minutes until piping hot.
Spoon into serving dish and sprinkle with cheese and parsley.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, oil and eggs together.
Pour half of the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour remainder of batter over sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Stir together cocoa, sugar, salt and hot water.
Bring to a slow boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add evaporated milk and water.
Serve with whipped cream or marshmallows.

title: chocolate dream cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into mixing bowl; blend well.
Place oleo, shortening, water and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to rapid boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients and add all at once to batter, mixing well. Pour into greased, lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2 pan and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until it tests done.
For a sheet cake, use a 16 x 11 x 1 pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes while preparing frosting.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, flour, spices and melted butter. Add pumpkin and milk last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 45 minutes in 325° oven.
To make two pies, I add extra egg and large can of pumpkin.

title: peach jam
directions: Rinse clean plastic containers and lids with boiling water. Peel and pit peaches; chop very fine.
Measure 2 1/4 cups into large bowl.
Add lemon juice.
Stir sugar into fruit.
Let stand 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Mix water and pectin in small saucepan.
Bring mixture to boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling and stirring 1 minute.
Stir pectin mixture into fruit mixture.
Stir until sugar dissolves, about 3 minutes.
Fill all containers quickly to within 1/2-inch of tops. Wipe off top edges of containers; cover with lids.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks or freeze extra container up to 1 year.

title: corn fritters
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, sugar and salt.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, milk, oil and creamed corn.
Blend in dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in whole kernel corn.
In deep fryer, drop batter by tablespoonfuls and fry in 2 to 3-inches hot oil for 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour over nuts.
Mix butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese; pour over (spread) cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies(dad's favorite)
directions: I just mix it all up in a big bowl and bake them at 350° until lightly brown around the edges.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: one dish potato salad and frankfurters
directions: Mix all ingredients together except franks.
Bring to boil, then place in oven and slowly bake at 350°, tightly covered, for 45 minutes.
Add franks; cook 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender in boiling water.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add meat; brown.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt, and tomato sauce.
Simmer gently 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and noodles.
Alternate noodles and meat in 2 quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Butter the bottom and sides of a 2-quart baking dish. Beginning with the ham, alternate layers of ham and potatoes, finishing with a layer of potatoes.
Combine the milk, mustard and onion.
Pour over all.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender. Remove cover and continue baking for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: onion cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, stir cream cheese until softened.
Add diced onion; mix together and pat into ball.
Roll in pecan pieces and place in airtight container in refrigerator for at least 24 hours before using.
Spread on crackers.

title: yummy cake
directions: Mix cake mix, chocolate pudding, oil, water and sour cream. Beat in eggs.
Fold in chocolate chips which have been coated with small amount of flour.
Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes as a sheet cake.
Can also be baked in a Bundt pan.

title: wassail
directions: For best results, be sure to begin the vinegar well in advance since you'll need to let it stand for a while to absorb the flavors.
Put the flavoring of your choice in clean bottles and fill them with plain wine vinegar.
Leave an inch free at the top if you need to insert a cork or glass stopper.

title: beef 'n' cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion.
Add cabbage, tomatoes, and chili beans.
Add enough water to almost cover cabbage.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on medium-low for 3 to 4 hours until cabbage is tender and water has cooked down some.
You will need a 6 to 8 quart pot to cook.
This does not taste like cabbage - Delicious!

title: zucchini cake
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to the squash, eggs, oil, raisins and walnuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Remove green rind and trim off red.
Cut into 2-inch pieces. Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse and steam until tender or nearly done.
Drain.
Combine remainder of ingredients and boil.
Add rinds and boil until clear.
Put rinds in jars. Boil syrup down thick before pouring over pieces.
Seal.
Red coloring may be added if desired.

title: chicken
directions: Skin chicken and cover with water.
Boil and remove when chicken is tender.
Let chicken cool; take 2 cups broth and put in medium saucepan.
Add cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cook on low heat until cheese melts.
Put spaghetti in rest of broth and cook. Chop onion, green pepper and drain mushrooms.
Put in small saucepan with small amount of butter.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt; simmer on low heat.
Drain spaghetti; put in ovenproof pan. Tear chicken up into small pieces and add to spaghetti.
Add to cheese mix, then add green pepper and mix.
Stir well.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cover pan and bake 30 minutes.
Remove; stir and let sit 15 minutes.

title: piroshki
directions: Make basic yeast rolls recipe.
Saute the ground beef and onion until browned.
Drain grease off.
Add other ingredients. Cool.
When bread is ready, cut with biscuit cutter and roll each out in a circle.

title: strawberry preserves deluxe
directions: Berries with hollow cores should not be used. Combine strawberries and sugar; let stand 3 to 4 hours. Bring slowly to boiling, stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves. Add lemon juice. Cook rapidly until berries are clear and syrup thick, about 10 to 12 minutes. Pour into a shallow pan. Let stand, uncovered, 12 to 24 hours in a cool place. Shake pan occasionally to distribute berries through syrup. Pack into hot Ball jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps. Process half pints and pints 20 minutes at 180° to 185° in hot water bath. Yield: About 4 half pints.

title: pat's brown raisin bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg well.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with raisins/water.
Stir well.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(Use greased bread pan.)

title: prune puff
directions: Separate eggs; beat egg whites very stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Continue beating; add prunes.
Beat until light.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 325° until nicely browned (20 to 25 minutes).

title: tasty tacos
directions: Thaw dough and slice into 3/4 to 1 inch slices.
Form a circle about 1/4 inch thick.
Fold in half and, using tongs, deep fry in oil until both sides are brown.
Make sure to hold open for ingredients while frying.
Fill with taco ingredients.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate a few hours.

title: chicken noodles
directions: Cook onions and sweet peppers in butter until clear.
Add to hot broth, mixed with soup.
Heat; stir in noodles.
Add chicken, pulled from bone; cook until tender.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot of water and cook about 4 hours until beans are tender and there is a gravy-like sauce. Serve in bowl over tortilla chips.
Garnish with lettuce, tomato, shredded cheese, sour cream, salsa and guacamole.

title: no crust pie
directions: Mix and put in glass dish. Bake at 300° until done.

title: candy cookies
directions: Combine the granulated sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk and bring to a rolling boil; boil for one minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and walnuts or coconut.
Drop from a teaspoon on wax paper.

title: quick beef and broccoli
directions: Slice steak diagonally across grain into thin strips.
Place in a shallow dish. Combine soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and sugar in a small bowl.
Pour over steak and set aside. Cut flowerets from broccoli. Cut stalks into thin slices.
Pour 2 tablespoons oil into wok or large skillet, coating bottom and sides.
Heat to medium-high (325°) for 1 minute. Add broccoli and onion. Stir-fry for 2 minutes. Remove from wok.
Pour remaining 1 tablespoon oil into wok, coating sides.
Add steak. Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in broccoli mixture. Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pea salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer all ingredients in order through onions.
Spread mayonnaise completely over top of onions. Sprinkle sugar then Parmesan cheese. Just a little. Add drained peas, then cover with grated cheese and sprinkle with bacon, then eat and enjoy!

title: *hard candy
directions: Mix together in saucepan the water, syrup and sugar.
Stir until sugar appears to be dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, until 300° on a candy thermometer is reached.
Wipe down sides of pan and add flavoring and coloring until evenly distributed.
Pour at once on a buttered and lightly sprinkled with 10x sugar cookie sheet.
As soon as it cools enough to handle, cut into small pieces and drop into a bowl.
Sprinkle again lightly with 10x sugar to prevent sticking together.
Makes about 1 pound.
For each different flavoring, use a different food coloring.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In a large bowl, stir together egg whites, banana, sugar and oil.
Stir flour mixture into banana mixture just until moistened.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Combine milk, vinegar, mayonnaise, sugar, Salad Supreme and pepper.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Toss with cabbage and carrot. Makes 2 cups dressing.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, water and peanuts until peanuts start popping; let pop two or three minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and soda.
Mix well and pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Do not try to spread!
Candy will be ready to break in about 10 minutes.

title: grandpa burton's vidalia pie
directions: Thinly slice the onions.
In large frying pan, saute bacon until crisp.
Drain the bacon of all grease and crumble it in bottom of pie shell.
In same pan, put in butter and onions and cook until they are slightly soft.
Stir occasionally.

title: cookie pie
directions: Melt enough butter or margarine to stick 3/4 of the crushed Oreos together.
Press firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat together the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip. Pour over Oreo crust.
Beat puddings and milk for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle remaining Oreo crumbs on top.
Refrigerate until pudding sets, then spoon and enjoy.

title: coca-cola steak
directions: Do not brown steak.
Cut into serving size pieces and place in a large shallow baking dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Peel and slice onion into thin slices and place over steak.
Pour catsup and Coke over steak.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: spicy sausage nacho dip
directions: Cook sausage, onion, and garlic until done; drain well. Place remaining ingredients in slow cooker on low heat. Cook until mixture is melted and hot (2-3 hours). Add meat mixture. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: vikki's fruit dip
directions: Blend well and chill.
Serve with pineapple chunks, sliced banana, green seedless grapes, fresh strawberries, apples slices or orange slices.

title: easy frozen fruit salad
directions: Cut peaches into chunks.
Slice bananas.
Combine all fruits with juice and freeze in a ring mold for 24 hours or overnight. Remove from mold and let thaw for 20 minutes before serving. Slice and serve.
If you have extra, freeze in small containers for leftovers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, mix chicken pieces, broth, soup and frozen vegetables.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour mixture over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix sour cream and soup.
Add onion, cheese and hash browns (uncooked).
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Chex with butter. Pour over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and pepper all together until tender.
Add a layer of squash and a layer of cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine shortening, salt, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 cup margarine or butter (1 stick).
Pour 1 cup of boiling water over mixture and stir until blended.
In a small bowl, sprinkle yeast and 1 teaspoon of sugar over 1/2 cup of warm water (105° to 115°).
Stir to mix slightly.
Let rest 5 minutes.
To mixture in a large bowl, add flour, eggs, yeast mixture and 1 cup of cold water, stirring to mix well.
Dough will be sticky.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 5 hours or overnight, stirring down dough if necessary.
On floured surface, roll half of the dough into an 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Melt 2 tablespoons of margarine or butter and spread over rectangle.
Spread 1 cup packed brown sugar on the margarine and sprinkle generously with ground cinnamon.
Beginning with long side, roll up jelly roll fashion.
Pinch the seam to seal.
Cut into 1-inch slices and place on 2 greased cookie sheets 1 inch apart.
Let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Frost with your favorite glaze.
Repeat with other half of dough.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Cover beans with water and add a pinch of baking soda.
Bring water to a boil and add 1 teaspoon shortening.
Cook beans until medium soft (20 to 30 minutes).
Fry the bacon partially to remove some of the fat; drain the beans, but save some of the juice in case the beans get dry during baking.
Mix the ingredients together; cover and bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: lanette's chicken pot pie
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Line casserole dish with one of the pastry shells.
Save the other for topping.
Remove bones from chicken.
Sprinkle chicken, chopped eggs, and vegetables throughout dish.
No need to mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix cream of chicken soup with 1 can of water.
Pour over chicken mixture.
May need to add more water, depending on how moist you like your pie.
Tear or cut the remaining pastry shell into strips.
Place across top of pie.
If baking in a round dish, place pastry on top but cut vents in shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart baking dish, layer sliced potatoes, 1 can cream of mushroom soup, 1 tablespoon butter or margarine, 1 can Cheddar cheese soup, chopped onion and 1/2 cup milk.
Continue layers until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring once after 1/2 hour of baking.
If potatoes are not tender after 1 hour, continue baking until potatoes are tender.

title: russian chicken
directions: Cook chicken in a skillet. Add Russian dressing, apricot marmalade and onion soup mix.
Simmer on low to marinate.
Serve over white rice.

title: best ever pumpkin bread
directions: Beat sugar and oil with eggs.
Add water and pumpkin.
Mix dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Stir in nuts and pour into well-greased loaf pans (makes 2 pans).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown ground beef; drain. Add onion and cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 45 to 60 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sour cream cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onion.
Combine all ingredients in a covered bowl.
Refrigerate until thoroughly blended.

title: super squash casserole
directions: Blend all the ingredients except bread crumbs.
Spread part of the crumbs on the bottom of the casserole and the rest on top of the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard crunch
directions: Mix melted oleo with flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and cinnamon. Stir until it's moist and crumbly.
Press half of this mixture into the 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Cover bottom mixture with the rhubarb.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Mix ingredients and spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake for 55 minutes to 1 hour until toothpick comes out clean.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash the avocados in a blender or food processor. Blend in remaining ingredients except tomatoes. After all is blended, fold in tomatoes.

title: pina colada cake
