directions: Bake according to directions in an oblong pan sprayed with Pam.
Punch holes in cake while hot.
Pour Eagle Brand over cake. Mix cream of coconut and coconut and pour over cake while hot. Cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Sprinkle some coconut over top.
Refrigerate.
Makes 12 servings.
Cake is best when refrigerated overnight.

title: cottage cheese dill bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water.
Stir to blend.
Stir in 2 teaspoons sugar.
Set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, onion, dill, baking powder, salt, 2 tablespoons sugar and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together as listed and drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, unsalted, until tender.
Pull from bones.
Melt butter and stir in stuffing mix.
Place a layer of chicken in casserole, then layer of mix.
Dilute mushroom soup with can of chicken broth. Pour over layers in casserole.
Place another layer of mix.
Dilute chicken soup with 1 can of broth and pour over all.
Put layer of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cake muffins("any idiot can cook")
directions: Mix together.
Put
in	ungreased muffin tins.	Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Freeze leftovers.

title: rice with mushrooms
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, saute onion in oil until golden brown. Add mushrooms; cook for 10 minutes.
Wash rice well.
Drop rice into 2 cups rapidly boiling salted water; bring to a brisk boil, stirring a few times; cook 1 minute.
Turn heat to the very lowest; cover pot tightly; cook for 20 minutes.
Do not remove cover to stir again.
The rice will absorb most of the liquid and will swell to near capacity without breaking.
Drain.
Rinse quickly under cold water.
Add rice to mushroom mixture; add 1/2 cup water, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: faye's cranberry bread
directions: Sift together flour and sugar. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. Combine orange juice and egg. Pour all at once with dry ingredients. Mix just enough to dampen; fold in nuts and cranberries. Spoon in greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown. Remove from pan. Cool. Store overnight for easy slicing.

title: simple seafood gumbo
directions: Combine beef stock, tomatoes, tomato paste and bay leaf in large saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Brown flour in a small amount of oil in saucepan.
Add celery, onion and green pepper.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add okra to stock mixture.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add shrimp.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add crab meat.
Salt and pepper. Cook for 30 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix margarine, flour, milk and sugar.
Pour in pan.
Add sweetened fruit and bake.

title: hot and tangy garlic chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips; coat with mixture of 1 tablespoon cornstarch, sherry and garlic.
Let stand 10 minutes. Combine broth, vinegar and red pepper with remaining cornstarch; set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in hot wok or skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Heat remaining oil in same pan over high heat.
Add vegetables; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Return chicken to pan with broth mixture.
Cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens.
Remove from heat; stir in soy sauce.
Serve immediately over pasta or rice (fettucini is best).
Serves 4.

title: hello dolly's squares
directions: Melt margarine in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Pour graham crumbs on top.
Add chips next layer and rest of ingredients.
Pour condensed milk on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lo-fat yummy
directions: Slice 1 inch layer off top of angel food cake.
Gently hollow out trench in cake 1 1/2 inches wide by 2 inches deep.
Tear cake from trench in small pieces.
Combine milk and pudding mix.
Beat on low speed of electric mixer 2 minutes.
Fold cake pieces and 1 3/4 cup of whipped topping into pudding.
Fill trench with mixture and replace top of cake.
Spread remaining topping over sides and top.
Chill before serving.

title: southern fried corn
directions: Fry bacon in skillet.
Remove bacon and add corn to drippings in skillet.
Crumble the bacon and add to the corn.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper and sugar to corn mixture.
Add peppers for flavoring, if desired.

title: pork chops with corn dressing
directions: Brown pork chops in shortening; place in a baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and form into 6 patties.
Place a patty on top of each chop.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: baked mac 'n' cheese
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, mustard and pepper.
Stir in macaroni.
In a cup, combine margarine and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield:
4 side dish servings.

title: spicy carrot snack cake
directions: Measure ingredients
listed in that order, except for carrots, chopped nuts and raisins, into a large bowl.
Blend 1 minute on low speed, 2 minutes on medium speed.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Toss apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix flour, shortening and water to make crust.
Roll out crust for a bottom and top layer. Put apple mixture on top of bottom crust in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Put top layer of crust on.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown, approximately 1 hour.

title: chinese-style beans
directions: Place beans in vegetable steamer and steam for 6 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Cool under cool running water and drain.
Mix soy sauce, water, cornstarch, sugar, sesame oil and crushed red pepper in a small bowl until the cornstarch is well blended.

title: cabbage-fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir into dissolved gelatin.
Chill until thickened.
Measure 1 1/2 cups thickened gelatin into a separate bowl.
Stir in pineapple and apples.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Combine mayonnaise and cabbage with remaining gelatin.
Pour into mold over the set gelatin.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish as desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Peel and grate cucumber.
Drain between paper towels.
Mix all ingredients well.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Add a few drops of green food coloring to give a cucumber color to mixture.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Set aside.
Prepare rice mix as directed.
Add chicken, cheese, olives, milk and onion to prepared rice.
Mix well.
Heat 5 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Add salt, cayenne pepper, lemon juice, garlic powder, onion and Tabasco; mix well.
Stir in chopped tomato.
Garnish with tomato wedges, if desired.
May be used as a dip, as a salad, served on a bed of lettuce, or as an appetizer to stuff cherry tomatoes.

title: savory sweet roast
directions: Brown meat on both sides in skillet.
Add onion.
Blend together remaining ingredients; pour over meat.
Cover and simmer for 2 1/2 hours, or until tender.

title: pepper and onion sandwich spread
directions: Grind bologna in food grinder or processor.
Add all other ingredients; mix together until of spreading consistency.
May need more or less mayonnaise.
Leftover ham may be used to make this spread, too.

title: fruit and cheese muffin
directions: On each of 2 plates, set 1 muffin half. Top each half with 1/3 cup cheese and spoon half of the pureed fruit over each portion. Sprinkle each with a dash of allspice.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Be sure it is completely mixed.
Pour into wide mouth gallon jar or pitcher and freeze for at least 24 hours.
Use scoop and put in glasses and pour more 7-Up or ginger ale over and stir slowly.
This is a very refreshing drink for a hot day.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chocolate mint dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan. In large mixer bowl, combine flour, sugar, butter, eggs and syrup; beat until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan; bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool completely in pan.
Spread Mint Cream Center on cake; cover and chill.
Pour Chocolate Topping over chilled dessert.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream the brown sugar and margarine.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake on a 13 x 15-inch cookie sheet at approximately 350° for 25 minutes.
As ovens vary, you will have to adjust time and temperature to your oven.
Let cool; cut into squares.
These freeze very well.

title: punch
directions: Place in a large pot and brew 3 to 4 hours.
Serve hot. Serves 30.

title: fried potatoes and okra
directions: Peel potatoes and either slice or dice. Place in iron frying pan with cooking oil (or bacon drippings).
Slice okra on top of potatoes and cook until tender.
You may cover pan to tender potatoes quickly.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef; add onions and green peppers and cook slowly until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thick enough to serve.
Skim off excess fat before canning.
Pour hot, into hot jars, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles.
Adjust caps. Process pints 1 hour at 10 pounds pressure.
Yields 8 pints.

title: chicken and potato casserole(low-fat)
directions: In a large nonstick skillet in 2 tablespoons liquid Butter Buds, saute white onions until nicely browned.
Remove and set aside with cooked chicken.
Add green pepper and garlic to skillet; saute 2 minutes.
Add more liquid Butter Buds, if necessary.
Stir in flour, salt, thyme and pepper.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until flour is browned, about 3 minutes.
Gradually stir in Burgundy and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken, mushrooms and onions.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.

title: pear bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat well. Add flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in pears and nuts.
Pour into two well-greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or bake in 5 mini loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad(here is another good salad made with pasta.)
directions: Cook spaghetti, rinse in cold water and drain.
Mix the Italian salad dressing and salad seasons (*Salad Supreme could be used in place of salad seasons), and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all the vegetables with the spaghetti, then pour in salad dressing.
Set bowl in refrigerator to marinate 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: macaroni loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes.

title: japanese pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix other ingredients and pour in two unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy pasta and vegetables
directions: Cook pasta per directions.
Puree cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and mint in processor.
Heat oil in large nonstick skillet. Add onion and garlic.
Cook 3 minutes until softened.
Add broccoli, red pepper, carrot and basil.
Cook 3 minutes; sprinkle with water to prevent sticking.
Add mushrooms.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Stir in peas; heat through.
Drain pasta.
Fold in cheese mixture.
Add vegetables.
Lightly mix to coat.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cream and butter in a saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until it forms a soft ball (small amount dropped in bowl of cold water).
Add vanilla, peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Pour into a buttered dish, refrigerate and cut into desired pieces.

title: baked steak
directions: Salt and pepper steak.
Brown on both sides.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 5 hungry men.

title: veal or chicken marsala
directions: Flour both sides.
Brown lightly in melted butter (both sides).
Meanwhile, dissolve bouillon cube in 1 cup hot water. Add sliced mushrooms to meat.
Add bouillon mix in pan.
Add the wine.
Blend well and cook on low heat 30 minutes.
Sauce will thicken as it cools.
Serve with spaghetti noodles and plain sauce (no meat) as a side dish and veal as your main dish on a separate serving dish.

title: dill pickles
directions: Fill a jar with pickles and dill.
Add salt, sugar and vinegar.
Fill remainder of jar with boiling water and seal.
Add garlic and pickling spices, if you wish.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a container and shake well. Refrigerate.

title: apple brownie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream topping.
Fruit may be added to top.

title: on hand bran muffins
directions: Put margarine in bowl with sugar, eggs and buttermilk, then mix in flour, baking soda, salt and Raisin Bran.
Mix well.
Fill baking cups in muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Baking mix can be stored up to a week in the refrigerator but do not stir after refrigerating.

title: easy hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients in an 8 x 10-inch Pyrex baking dish and bake in a 400° oven until bubbly and slightly brown on top.
Serve while hot with a favorite cracker or bagel chips.

title: chicken florentine fettuccine
directions: Saute butter, mushrooms, onions and garlic powder until tender; set aside.
In a medium saucepan, mix soup, cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and cayenne pepper.
Heat on medium-low heat until creamy.
Cook fettuccine as directed and drain.
In a large bowl or pan, toss chicken, spinach, soup and cheese mixture, mushrooms, onions and fettuccine until well mixed.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
(You may need to use an 8 x 8-inch pan, also.) Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat iron skillet on medium-high heat with a few drops of oil. Cook tortillas about 20 seconds on each side; set aside.

title: hot barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in pan and simmer 10 minutes.
Use as a marinade or spoon over cooked meat right on the plate!

title: pineapple and buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple to dissolve Jell-O.
Allow to chill until almost set.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill until congealed.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and drain off fat.
Add onion and garlic and cook 2 minutes more.
Then add seasonings and soup and cook for 10 minutes, covered.
Add rice and mix well, then bake for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese and melt.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion and celery in butter and pour over thawed broccoli in casserole dish.
On top of broccoli, layer the Minute rice, soup and cheese spread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Leave cream cheese and butter at room temperature.
Mix together butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add crushed crackers.
Mix well and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Set aside.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients and chill 1 hour.

title: mixed frenze
directions: Brown beef and onion in large skillet.
Drain off excess fat. Stir in franks, pepperoni, Ragu and mustard.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into split, hollowed out submarine or hard rolls.
Top with grated cheese. Place on foil pans or heavy-duty foil.
Cover loosely and heat until rolls are warm and cheese melts.
Makes 5 to 6 submarine rolls.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Split shrimp on curved side; do not cut completely through. Remove shell and black vein; wash and pat dry.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Stuff each shrimp.
Place on baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and molasses thoroughly.
Stir in water.
Measure flour.
Blend all dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Chill.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch round cutter.
Place far apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes or until no imprint remains when touched lightly.
Frost cooled cookies with creamy icing.
Makes 2 2/3 dozen cookies.

title: triple layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish) baking pan.
Melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine or butter.
Top evenly with coconut, then Eagle Brand.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
In saucepan, over low heat melt chips with peanut butter.
Spread evenly over hot coconut layer. Cool 30 minutes.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into bars.

title: yeast bread
directions: Place water, oil and egg in a large mixing bowl and stir with a fork until egg is mixed.
Sprinkle 3 cups of white flour over liquid in bowl and do not stir.
Scatter dry yeast over flour. Mix and beat with a spoon.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix with hands if necessary.
Place in greased kettle, cover and let rise at least to double bulk.
Divide into four portions.
Knead on floured board.
Shape and place in 4 greased loaf tins.
Let rise until slightly above tops of pans.
Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven. Brush tops with oleo.
Cool on racks completely before placing in plastic bag.

title: beets in orange sauce
directions: Drain beets.
Mix sugar, lemon juice, butter, orange juice, salt and pepper in a double boiler.
Heat.
Mix cornstarch and cold water.
Stir into orange juice mixture; cook until slightly thickened.
Add drained beets to orange juice and heat thoroughly.

title: vera's dijon herb chicken
directions: Saute chicken in butter in a skillet over medium heat for 10 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken to a serving platter. Reserve pan drippings in skillet.
Keep chicken warm.
Add lemon juice and next 3 ingredients to pan drippings.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chives and parsley.
Pour over chicken.
Yields 8 servings.

title: southern oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. In another bowl, sift flour, salt and soda. Add pecans and oatmeal. Mix all together. Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: herb and garlic pork roast
directions: Pound garlic with salt to form a smooth paste.
Add parsley and pound until incorporated.
Stir in paprika and oregano, then gradually stir in olive oil to form thick, oily but not homogenous mixture.
Rub mixture over pork loin, then cover and refrigerate at least overnight or for up to 2 days, turning loin from time to time.
Bring to room temperature before roasting.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour 1/2 teaspoon melted butter in baking
dish.
Spoon
on
thick blackberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: minnesota swedish meatballs
directions: In large bowl, mix together first 9 ingredients.
Shape into balls and brown in frypan.
Mix together salad oil, flour and paprika and pour this over browned meatballs.
Mix together remaining ingredients to make a cream sauce.
Pour this over meatballs and simmer until thick.

title: fruit tea
directions: Let tea bags steep in hot water for 5 minutes. Add juices and sugar and stir. Put in refrigerator and get cold. Add 1/2 liter of ginger ale or 7-Up (or more if you like) when ready to serve.

title: practically foolproof meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add marshmallow cream, beating until soft peaks form.
Spread over pie filling, sealing to edge of crust.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of a double boiler; heat until melted.
Combine cake mix, remaining evaporated milk and butter; mix until mixture holds together. Stir in nuts.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter, egg, vanilla and almond extract. Mix in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough into halves.
Roll each half 3/16-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut into shapes.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Place on lightly greased sheet.
Bake until edges are lightly brown, approximately 7 to 8 minutes.

title: mr. peterson's barbecue sauce
directions: Beat egg with poultry seasoning.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients except apples, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Beat thoroughly.
Slice apples, mix sugar and cinnamon.
Pour half of batter into greased tube pan, place half of apples on batter and sprinkle with half of the cinnamon sugar mixture.
Repeat layers with other half of batter, apples and cinnamon sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy easy - yummy yummy fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve with all of your favorite fruits!

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar, flour and cocoa. Pour margarine into sugar mixture. Stir. Add eggs, one at a time, stirring well after each addition. Add milk and vanilla. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set. Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; blend until chopped. Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.
Each tablespoon contains about 8 calories.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, pour peaches with juice and extract.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly on top.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle on nuts, if desired.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°
until brown and crusty.
Delicious!

title: fancy potatoes
directions: Parboil or steam potatoes until almost cooked.
Peel potatoes and grate.
Put melted butter in an 8 x 8-inch pan and add grated potatoes.
Pour half and half cream to cover bottom half of potatoes.
Bake at 350° until the cream is absorbed by potatoes (approximately 45 minutes).
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top and place back in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix in a bowl the confectioners sugar, margarine and cream cheese.
In a separate bowl, combine the cold milk and instant vanilla pudding.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Mix contents of the two bowls together until smooth; allow to set.
Layer crumbs and mixture into an 8-inch flowerpot or pail (as in pail and shovel). End with crumb mixture.
Freeze in freezer overnight.

title: spicy carrot cake
directions: Combine ingredients, adding egg whites last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes before taking out of pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first
ingredients
well and press into pie pan. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Fill with remaining ingredients.
Makes a large pie.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken, save broth.
Take chicken from bones and layer in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Pour broth over.
Spread soup over (may be made ahead to this point and refrigerated).
When ready to bake, make a mixture of the margarine, flour and milk, stirring until smooth.
Pour over top of pie and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes, or until crust rises and turns golden brown.

title: simple microwave fudge
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter in microwave for 2 minutes. Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan or dish.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: cheese casserole with tortillas
directions: Place in dish in layers.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes. Simple, but delicious.

title: pumpkin roll cake
directions: Beat eggs on High speed of mixer for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in the sugar.
Stir in the pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and pumpkin pie spice.
Fold into pumpkin.
Spread on greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 375°
for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Starting at narrow end roll towel and cake together; cool and unroll.

title: granny goo cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts over crust.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: plain doughnuts
directions: Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Put on bread board and knead. Cut with dough
cutter about 1/4-inch thick, then heat fat with 2 or 2 1/2 pounds
lard
or
Crisco.	Cook at 350° or 375°.

title: stuffed baked potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes until tender and drain. Place in casserole dish. Brown bacon strips until crisp.
Blend potatoes.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix. Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° just until cheese is melted or put in microwave to melt.

title: twinkie pie
directions: Arrange Twinkies in dish.
Make pudding as directed on box. Pour over the Twinkies.
Next, spread Cool Whip on top.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger and oats.
Chop finely the onion and carrots. Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour in greased baking pan.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in olive oil or butter until tender. Add bay leaf.

Add beef and brown, stirring frequently. Add tomato paste and water. Add all other ingredients. Bring mixture to a boil. Boil hard for 10 minutes. Simmer 3 to 4 hours. Remove bay leaf before serving over pasta.

title: baked green beans
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, stir soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper until smooth.
Mix in green beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together cream of mushroom soup and sour cream. Boil boneless chicken until done. After chicken cooks, tear into small pieces. Add to soup and sour cream. Pour into baking dish. Top with stuffing. Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: relish dip
directions: Blend well and chill.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.
Serve with green peppers, radishes, carrots, cauliflower and celery.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form meatballs.
Brown meatballs evenly on medium heat for about 5 minutes.
Add Marinara sauce and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over pasta or rice.

title: easy turkey burritos
directions: Brown turkey & onion in large skillet, drain fat. Add chilies, salsa, chopped tomatoes and refried beans. Simmer for 20-30 minutes on low heat. Salt & Pepper to taste.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt margarine in heavy pan; add oysters and 1/2 cup oyster liquid.
Heat until oysters curl.
Combine milk, cream, salt, pepper and sauces in second pan.
Heat until bubbles appear.
Pour in first pan with oysters.
Add remaining oyster liquid.
Heat thoroughly; sprinkle with paprika and float margarine on top. Serve hot.

title: serendipity apple pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and place 1/4 of these in bottom of pie pan on the unbaked crust. Shred 2 peeled apples (long thin shreds) over dry ingredients. Repeat layer of dry ingredients, layer of 3 apples and layer of dry ingredients. Pour half and half around edge and dot center with butter. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 40 minutes. Serve with cream (ice cream?).

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a casserole dish, sides and bottom.
In a bowl combine hash browns, 1 stick of melted butter, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, onion, cheese, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and spread evenly.
Take 1/2 stick melted butter and pour over the top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour or until top gets brown.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse all beans; combine with green pepper, celery and onion.
Combine last 7 ingredients and heat.
Pour sauce over vegetables while hot.
Drain before serving.
Should be made at least 24 hours before serving.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add egg and mix well.
Add oil and mix well.
Add oatmeal, cornflakes, coconut, nuts and mix. Add flour mixture (flour, soda and salt) and vanilla.
Mix well and chill.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets. Press with fork to flatten.
Bake at 325 ° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool before removing from cookie sheet to prevent crumbling.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a large bowl.
Add margarine (cut margarine into 4 or 5 chunks and place around the top of sugar). Add milk and cook in microwave for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, until butter melts.
Stir in vanilla and nuts; pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Let cool and slice.

title: smoked ham or turkey(to be cooked in charcoal smoker.)
directions: Season meat and rub with oil.
Soak 5 charcoals in charcoal lighter.
Place in pan of smoker and light.
Allow the 5 charcoals to turn white.
Put 1/2 of the 20 pound bag of charcoal on top of the original 5 charcoals.
Put these in gently by hand.
Do not dump quickly.
Install water pan and fill with water.
Install bottom grill.
Fill bottom rack first, if needed.
If you are only doing one meat, use the top rack only.
Cover with lid.
Allow to cook for 8 to 10 hours.
After 8 hours, check water.
Add water, if needed.
You may also add more charcoal at this time and leave meat on smoker until you are ready to eat.
Meat will not dry out as long as you keep water in pan.
It's best to smoke meat at night while you're sleeping and it will be ready in the morning (you may also add hickory chips for extra flavor, if wanted).

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix well.
Heat at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: frozen cabbage
directions: Chop up the cabbage and sprinkle with the salt.
Let stand for one hour.
Squeeze the juice our of the cabbage.
Add the carrot and pepper.

title: premium bonbons
directions: Place peanut butter chips, chocolate chips, butter and chopped chocolate in medium saucepan; cook over very low heat until chips and chocolate are melted, stirring frequently to blend.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Stir in cracker crumbs gradually to make a stiff "dough." Roll into large marble size balls.
Spread pecan meal on waxed paper; roll each bonbon in meal to coat.
If desired, press a pecan piece into top of each ball.
Let stand on waxed paper 30 minutes.
Store in airtight container at room temperature or in freezer, bringing back to room temperature to serve.
Makes 50.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place desired fruit in bottom of pan.
Melt oleo and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread evenly over fruit.
Punch holes in dough.
Mix 1/2 cup water and 1 cup sugar.
Pour over top of dough.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple-cheese salad
directions: Mix jello, hot water, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Set to a heavy syrup.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal bread for bread machine
directions: Follow instructions for Bread Menu.
Insert mixing blade in bread pan.
Measure ingredients into bread pan.
Place pan in bread maker.
Select bread setting; push start button.
Beeper sounds when cycle is completed.
Remove pan and bread.
Excellent sandwich bread.

title: szechuan green beans
directions: Cook beans and salt 3 minutes; drain.
Uncover.
Set on cool burner.
Saute the onion, pepper and sesame seed in oil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from the fire.
Combine green beans and sauteed onion, etc.
Add oyster sauce.
Cool, uncovered, for 1/2 hour before covering to carry to luncheon.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Allow ice cream to soften.
Stir in pie crust.
Add fudge and caramel topping.
Swirl it around, then add candy bar pieces, then Cool Whip.
You can decorate with pecan pieces and cherries. Freeze.

title: mystery cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts and brown sugar. Stir until moist and top with a mixture of nuts and brown sugar.
Bake in an 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Reserve 1 c. of tomato sauce. Combine all other ingredients. Place in 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Heat reserved tomato sauce and serve with meat loaf.

title: pear cake
directions: Chop
pears.
Add
1/2 cup sugar; set aside for 1 hour. Beat eggs;
add	sugar,	vanilla
and
cooking oil.
Sift the flour, soda,
salt and spice together and add to egg mixture. Add chopped pears and pecans; mix well.
Preheat oven to 325°. Pour
batter into tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: noodles
directions: Mix and roll out thin.
Cut into 1/4-inch strips and dry overnight.
Drop into boiling broth.
Thicken with 1 tablespoon cornstarch mixed with 1 tablespoon water.

title: butterscotch sticks
directions: Melt morsels and add peanuts
and
potato sticks.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper-covered cookie sheets.
Refrigerate to harden.

title: baked cream of chicken
directions: Spray 9 x 12-inch dish with nonstick cooking spray. Coat chicken with Shake 'n Bake. Bake for 1 hour. Dilute chicken soup and pour over chicken. Bake 15 or 20 more minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut up chicken and add the rest of the ingredients, plus 1/2 to 1 cup of the broth (except the potato chips).
Pour into a casserole dish and top with potato chip crumbs.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: nutritious candy pick-ons for kids
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl (it's sticky at first). Roll in bite size balls.
You can roll the balls in crushed nuts, if you like, or even add shredded coconut and raisins.
No cooking and very nutritious.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Place bread in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish one layer of sausage and one layer of cheese.
Beat eggs with dry ingredients.
Add milk and beat.
Pour over layers.
Place in refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator; let stand 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, then 350° for 15 minutes longer.

title: million dollar chili
directions: In a large kettle, melt beef suet.
Add garlic and onions. Cook until golden.
Add green pepper and meat, breaking up until crumbly.
Spoon off liquid.
Mix in salt, pepper and tomatoes. Add beans, chili powder, cumin, oregano, paprika and wine, mixing after each addition.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Cool; refrigerate 2 days.
When ready to use, skim fat off top and reheat slowly.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a buttered 8 x 8 pan place rice and water.
Sprinkle with soup mix and place chicken on top.
Add can of chicken soup mixed with 1 can of water.
Bake covered for 1 hour or until nicely browned at 350°.

title: special 'k' cookies
directions: Bring sugar and white Karo syrup to boil; let boil 1 to 2 minutes.
To boiled mixture, add peanut butter; mix well.
Pour mixture over Special K cereal.
Mix and press into a 12 x 16-inch pan.

title: roast beef
directions: Place roast on foil, mix all ingredients; pour over meat. Wrap and place in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: potato donuts
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar and shortening. Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to egg mixture alternately with potatoes (dough should be smooth).
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: cheese rice
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Combine with butter, milk, cheese and rice and seasonings and mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into rice mixture.
Bake in 350° oven in buttered baking dish, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, milk, egg, soup mix, corn flakes or oats, salt and pepper.
Form into loaf; shape in casserole.
Mix brown sugar, mustard and catsup.
Spread on top of meat loaf.
Microwave 12 to 14 minutes uncovered.
Rotate 1 time.
Remove and put wax paper over meat loaf for a few minutes.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Do not preheat the oven.
Cream sugars, shortening and butter together.
Add the eggs one at a time.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder together and add alternately with the milk.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours (when toothpick comes out clean).

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together oatmeal and water and let set 30 minutes. "Smash" together remaining ingredients and bake at 350° in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for about 45 minutes.
Three-quarter cup chopped nuts or raisins may be added.
Serve as is or with a butter frosting.

title: nonfattening sauce for pasta
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour all of the cans of fruit with the juice into a large bowl.
Add sliced bananas; stir in both boxes of pudding (just the powder, do not fix pudding as directed).
Mix pudding and fruit until all mixed, set in refrigerator until cooled and eat and enjoy.

title: sunday dinner chicken
directions: Sprinkle rice in a greased casserole dish. Cover with chicken. Do not add salt. Sprinkle chicken with onion soup mix. Cover with canned soup. Add water. Use a tight-fitting lid or aluminum foil and bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: In a large skillet fry the bacon and sausage until brown.
Add the onions and bell pepper.
Cook 5 minutes. Combine the chili powder, cumin and red pepper flakes or Tabasco sauce and add to ingredients. Cook 5 minutes. Combine the brown sugar, regular sugar and cider vinegar.
Cook 5 minutes. Add the beans and cook 15 minutes.

title: corn, okra and tomato
directions: Cook and stir okra in 1 stick margarine in a large skillet over medium heat until tender.
Add corn and 2 tablespoons margarine. Cook uncovered until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook uncovered until tomatoes are hot.
Serve.

title: nita's amish potato patties
directions: Peel, wash and grate potatoes.
Peel, wash and chop onion. In a mixer bowl slightly beat eggs, salt, pepper and flour. Squeeze liquid out of potatoes and add potatoes to egg mixture. Stir in parsley.
Drop by spoonfuls into a hot greased skillet. Do not make too thin because you will not be able to turn them over.
Cook until browned on both sides, about 3 minutes on each side or until tests done.
Use as breakfast pancakes or as bread for a meal.

title: squash cakes
directions: Combine ingredients except oil.
Mix well and drop mixture into hot oil.
Brown on both sides.

title: shirley's fried pies
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add shortening, then egg and milk.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Take pieces of dough size of large marble.
Roll.
Cut round circle size of large saucer.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons very stiff filling (your choice).
Brush 1/2 of edge with water.
Fold over.
Crimp edges together with fork and deep fry until golden brown.

title: oatmeal cookie bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press all but 1 cup mix into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread 1 1/2 to 2 cups fruit preserves or apple butter over mix.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs of mix over preserves. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes (until golden brown).
Cool and cut into bars.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat until creamy mushroom soup, Knox gelatine and 1/4 cup water.
Add mayonnaise, cream cheese, crab and/or shrimp.
Add chopped onions, bell peppers and celery to taste.
Pour into mold and set at least overnight.
Serve with Waverly crackers.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake in pie shell for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Shape into 20 meatballs using a rounded tablespoonful for each.
Brown well in shortening. Drain excess fat.
Sprinkle flour over meatballs; stir gently to coat meatballs.
Combine tomatoes, 57 Sauce, sugar and salt; pour over meatballs.
Simmer, uncovered, 25 minutes or until sauce is desired consistency, stirring occasionally.
Serve meatballs and sauce over noodles.
Makes 5 servings (about 3 cups sauce).

title: favorite meat marinade
directions: Score meaty side of ribs.
Place meat in plastic bag. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: zucchini cobbler
directions: Combine until crumbly.
Press 1/2 mixture (approx. 3 1/2 cups) into a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Follow with zucchini mixture and topping.
Bake 30 - 40 minutes at 350° degrees until lightly browned.

title: gooies
directions: Mix together
and press evenly into 12 x 18-inch baking sheet. May sprinkle nuts over this, if desired.

title: quick peach pie
directions: Place sliced peaches in a pie plate and sprinkle a little sugar over them to keep them from turning brown.
Cut each slice of bread into 4 fingers and weave into a lattice crust on top of peaches. Mix sugar, flour, melt butter, egg and flavorings well.
Coat crust with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6; 17 grams fat, 394 calories.

title: griddle cakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk.
Mix dry ingredients together and then add to egg and milk.
Add melted margarine.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: snoball cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine nuts, butter and powdered sugar until mixture is fluffy.
Mix in vanilla.
Add flour; beat until well blended.
Roll into balls (1-inch).
Place on cookie sheet; bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar while warm, then again when cool.
